| ABOUT THIS DOCUMENT 

This document will serve as the basis for which the functional specification for website features. The entire scope for each feature may still require refining from both a client facing perspective but also from an eWave internal development technical perspective.

Assumptions and open questions are indicated within each feature in the section that follows and are ideally confirmed and answered respectively prior to the creation of the development specification.

| GLOSSARY

  1. SECTION STATUSES

Please find below clarification of the section status flow:

STATUS

DESCRIPTION

NEW

Sections marked with this status are only added for the matter of structure, work on these sections will be scheduled and planned.

WIP

Work in progress status means that the section is currently in progress on eWave side and no action is expected from BAT team

PENDING

Sections marked with this status are ready for review by the BAT team and might have open questions that are waiting for feedback. For the sections in this status, corresponding Basecamp thread will be marked in comment, and once formal ‘APPROVED’ will be obtained via basecamp,  all requirements in this section will be considered as approved and ready for development.

  1. MAGENTO VERSION (APPROVED)

Version:  Commerce (Enterprise edition) 2.3.5p1

Minimum server requirements:

http://devdocs.magento.com/guides/v2.0/install-gde/system-requirements.html 

Please note that once we kick-off development, the version of Magento used will be locked for the duration of the project MVP phase to ensure compatibility and continuity of all customisations that are implemented.

The upgrade to the newest version of Magento might be considered after careful change control, and would typically only be required based on critical security update requirements.

  1. WEBSITE STRUCTURE (APPROVED)

Every Magento installation has a hierarchy of website(s), store(s), and store view(s). The term “scope” determines where in the hierarchy a database entity — such as a product, attribute, or category — content element, or configuration setting applies. Websites, stores, and store views have one-to-many parent/child relationships. A single installation can have multiple websites, and each website can have multiple stores and store views.

Website:

Multiple websites can be set up that use the same Magento installation. The websites can be set up to use the same domain, or different domains. If you want each store to have a dedicated checkout process under its own domain, each store must have a distinct IP address and separate security certificate.

WEBSITE NAME

CODE

SORT ORDER

VELO ID Website

 velo_id

VELO ID Store

Store:

A single installation of Magento can have multiple stores that share the same Admin. Stores that are under the same website have the same IP address and domain, use the same security certificate, and share a single checkout process.

The important thing to understand is that the stores use the same Magento code, and share the same Admin. Each store can have a separate catalog, or share the same catalog.

  1. CATEGORY TREE STRUCTURE (APPROVED)

Before you add products to your catalog, you need to establish the basic category structure of your catalog. Every product must be assigned to at least one category. Categories are usually created in advance, before products are added to the catalog. However, you can also add categories “on the fly” while creating a product.

Link to the category tree is here.

  1. PRODUCTS ATTRIBUTES AND SETS (APPROVED)

Attributes are the building blocks of your product catalog, and describe specific characteristics of a product. Product attributes can be organized into attribute sets, which are then used as templates for creating products.

Attributes determine the type of input control that is used for product options, provide additional information for product pages, and are used as search parameters and criteria for layered navigation, product comparison reports, and promotions. You can create as many attributes and attribute sets as necessary to describe the products in your catalog. In addition to the attributes that you can create, system attributes, such as price, are built into the core Magento platform and cannot be changed.

One of the first steps when creating a product is to choose the attribute set that is used as a template for the product record. The attribute set determines the fields that are available during data entry, and the values that appear to the customer.

The attributes are organized into groups that determine where they appear in the product record. Your store comes with an initial attribute set called “default” which includes a set of commonly-used attributes. If you would like to add only a small number of attributes, you can add them to the default attribute set. However, if you sell products that require specific types of information, such as cameras, it might be better to create a dedicated attribute set that includes the specific attributes that are needed to describe the product.

More details on Product attributes could be found here: https://docs.magento.com/user-guide/stores/attributes-product.html 

Link to product attribute specification is here.

  1. CONSUMER PROFILE AND ADDRESS ATTRIBUTES (APPROVED)

Customer attributes provide the information that is required to support the order, fulfillment, and customer management processes. Because your business is unique, you might need fields in addition to those provided by the system. You can add custom attributes to the Account Information, Address Book, and Billing Information sections of the customer’s account. Customer address attributes can also be used in the Billing Information section during checkout, or when guests register for an account.

More details about customer attributes could be found here: https://docs.magento.com/user-guide/stores/attributes-customer.html 

File/link to customer profile attributes is here.

  1.  VELO UAE WEB-SITE

  1. SERVER ENVIRONMENTS (APPROVED)

VELO UAE web-site will be hosted in the same way as Velo Indonesia web-site.

One Magento instance will be used to manage Velo Indonesia, Pakistan, UAE, Glo Philippines web-sites.

  1. MAGENTO VERSION (APPROVED)

VELO UAE will be on the same Magento version as Velo Indonesia, Pakistan, Glo Philippines. In case of a Magento version upgrade, all markets will be upgraded simultaneously hence they both are inside one Magento instance.

  1. WEBSITE STRUCTURE (APPROVED)

Every Magento installation has a hierarchy of website(s), store(s), and store view(s). The term “scope” determines where in the hierarchy a database entity — such as a product, attribute, or category — content element, or configuration setting applies. Websites, stores, and store views have one-to-many parent/child relationships. A single installation can have multiple websites, and each website can have multiple stores and store views.

Website:

Multiple websites can be set up that use the same Magento installation. The websites can be set up to use the same domain, or different domains. If you want each store to have a dedicated checkout process under its own domain, each store must have a distinct IP address and separate security certificate.

WEBSITE NAME

CODE

SORT ORDER

DEFAULT STORE

VELO AE Website

velo_ae

3

VELO AE Store

Store:

A single installation of Magento can have multiple stores that share the same Admin. Stores that are under the same website have the same IP address and domain, use the same security certificate, and share a single checkout process.

The important thing to understand is that the stores use the same Magento code, and share the same Admin. Each store can have a separate catalog, or share the same catalog.

Store view:

Store views are typically used to make the store available in different locales. Shoppers can use the language chooser in the header of the store to change the store view.

  1. WEBSITE PRICE FORMAT (APPROVED)

  • General
  • Stores > Configuration
  • > General > Country Options
  • Default Country - UAE
  • Allow Countries - UAE
  • > General > Locale Options
  • Timezone - Gulf Standard Time (GMT + 4)
  • Locale -  ar-ae  English
  • Weight Unit - Kgs
  • First Day of Week - Sunday

  • Store Name - VELO
  • Store Phone Number - 8000-Velo (8356)

  • Base Currency - AED

  • Enabled - No

  • > Sales > Minimum Order Amount

  • > Tax > Calculation Settings
  • Catalog Prices - Including Tax
  • Shipping Prices - Including Tax
  • Apply Discount On Prices - Including Tax

  • Default Country - UAE

  1. PAYMENT METHOD  (APPROVED)

  1. FEATURE CHECK-LIST (APPROVED)

Features that will be enabled and disalbed on the VELO UAE site can be found here in “VELO UAE” column.

  • Features that with “unticked” state will be disabled on VELO UAE storefront
  • Features that with “ticked” state will reuse the Above Market Core AS IS features on VELO UAE website
  • Customization to allow disabling the Registration feature on VELO UAE will be prioritised in Above Market Release, feature request to be submitted by BAT to the backlog. It won’t be reflected on VELO UAE website until this feature is ready on Above market Release. Feature details can be found here

  1. [PIII] [BAT-II-0279] VUSE KSA WEB-SITE (PENDING)

  1. SERVER ENVIRONMENTS (PENDING)

  1. MAGENTO VERSION (PENDING)

VUSE KSA will be on the same Magento version as Velo Indonesia, Pakistan, Glo Philippines websites. In case of a Magento version upgrade, all markets will be upgraded simultaneously hence they are inside one Magento instance.

  1. WEBSITE STRUCTURE (PENDING)

Every Magento installation has a hierarchy of website(s), store(s), and store view(s). The term “scope” determines where in the hierarchy a database entity — such as a product, attribute, or category — content element, or configuration setting applies. Websites, stores, and store views have one-to-many parent/child relationships. A single installation can have multiple websites, and each website can have multiple stores and store views.

Website:

Multiple websites can be set up that use the same Magento installation. The websites can be set up to use the same domain, or different domains. If you want each store to have a dedicated checkout process under its own domain, each store must have a distinct IP address and separate security certificate.

WEBSITE NAME

CODE

SORT ORDER

DEFAULT STORE

VUSE SA Website

vuse_sa

6

VUSE SA Store

Store:

A single installation of Magento can have multiple stores that share the same Admin. Stores that are under the same website have the same IP address and domain, use the same security certificate, and share a single checkout process.

The important thing to understand is that the stores use the same Magento code, and share the same Admin. Each store can have a separate catalog, or share the same catalog.

  1. PRODUCT CAROUSELS (DESKTOP)

CAROUSEL BEHAVIOR:

  • Products will be displayed in a line, max 4 product tiles product tiles will be displayed fully, on right side next to the forth product tile one more product will be displayed partially (if there are any), this will give the user an idea that there are more products per line
  • If less than max visible amount of products assigned, product tiles will be left aligned
  • If more than max visible amount of products assigned:
  • arrows will appear for the user to navigate
  • upon click carousel will be shifted by 1 product to the left or right, depending on the clicked arrow
  • progress slider bar will appear at the bottom, showing the current progress on the carousel
  • carousel will not be looped

VISUAL EXAMPLE:

RESOLUTION

DESIGN

DESKTOP

  1. PRODUCT CAROUSELS (MOBILE)

CAROUSEL BEHAVIOR:

  • Max 2 product tiles will be displayed fully, on right side next to the second product tile next product will be displayed partially (if there are any, this will give the user an idea that there are more products)
  • If less than max visible amount of products assigned, product tiles will be left aligned
  • If there is more than max visible amount of products assigned,:
  • user will be able to swipe to navigate between product tiles
  • progress slider bar will appear at the bottom, showing the current progress on the carousel
  • carousel will not be looped

VISUAL EXAMPLE:

RESOLUTION

DESIGN

MOBILE

  1. PRODUCT TILE

PRODUCT TILE ELEMENTS:

  • Each product tile will consist of the following elements:
  1. product image (small)
  2. product name - if too long, will be cut with ellipsis
  3. product price - if discounted, will go two lines
  • Upon click on (a.) product image or (b.) products name on the product tile, user will be redirected to product details page of this product

  1. [GPH-US036] PRODUCT TILE CUSTOM ADJUSTMENT (APPROVED)

PRODUCT TILE ELEMENTS:

  • Each product tile on Product List page will consist of the following extra elements based on the regular Product Tile
  • configuration selection - if available
  • “add to basket” button
  • Configuration product - if available
  • Upon selecting an option from “configuration selection”  and clicking on “add to basket”, the selected product will be added to the shopping cart
  • Upon clicking on “add to basket” without selecting any configuration option, user will be redirected to the product details page
  • Simple product
  • Upon clicking on the “add to basket” button, the selected product will be added to the shopping cart

  1. “SOFT AGE VERIFICATION” POP-UP (APPROVED)

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT115

I want user to confirm that he/she is 18 or over years old before browsing web-site content, so that people under legal age won't be able to see the content and products on the web-site

BAT116

I want to 'remember' user's choice of age, when he/she is 18 or over, so that I won't ask to confirm it during one user session upon each page reload

BAT117

I want to be redirected to Google default page if I'm under legal age, so that I won't be stuck on the pop-up when my age is under 18

POP-UP BEHAVIOR:

  • User won’t be able to close pop-up without selecting age ‘option’
  • Page underneath pop-up won’t be scrollable and will have dark overlay
  • Pop-up will be displayed on any page, not only when user is targeting Homepage
  • Upon click, user will:
  • if ‘I AM 18 OR OVER’ is clicked ->
  • pop-up will be closed
  • user will be able to browse web-site content
  • user’s choice will be ‘remembered’ and user won’t see this pop-up again if we have information about user’s choice
  • if ‘I AM UNDER 18’ is clicked ->
  • user will be redirected to https://www.google.com/ 
  • if user will go back to the web-site again, pop-up will be displayed
  • Pop-up content (text, buttons and links) won’t be manageable in admin panel

POP-UP TEXT:

Title: Untuk mengakses website ini, Anda harus berusia 18 tahun atau lebih

Paragraph: Tolong verifikasi umur Anda terlebih dahulu, apakah Anda telah berusia 18 tahun atau lebih?

Buttons: Ya (corresponds to I AM 18 OR OVER button on the design), Tidak (corresponds to I AM UNDER 18 button on the design)

Small text below buttons: Website ini mengandung informasi mengenai produk nikotin yang bersifat adiktif. Website ini ditujukan bagi pengguna produk nikotin yang berusia 18 tahun atau lebih dan bertempat tinggal di Indonesia.

BAT-II-0020-US1

As a user, I want to see the full screen Soft age verification pop-up

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  • The Soft Age verification pop-up will cover the user’s full screen and the page content won’t be visible.
  • A user won’t be able to close pop-up without selecting age ‘option’.
  • Pop-up content (text, CTA buttons) should be manageable via CMS block.
  • Admin should be able to manage the background of the pop-up and use images as a background.
  • Admin should be able to change the layout and spacing of the pop-up

  1. [Plll] [BAT-ll-0154] AUDIT IMPROVEMENT - TIMER TO SHOW SOFT AGE VERIFICATION

FEATURE HIGHLIGHTS:

“SOFT AGE VERIFICATION” POP-UP (APPROVED)

Are there any dependencies with Integrations or 3rd party systems?

(If yes, all systems are to be mentioned here and details are to be described in the functional or non-functional requirements when applicable)

No

Applicable for both logged in and guest users?

Yes

Market or Core?

(If Market, this Feature will not be available to any further enablement for any other market, rather than a specified one)

CORE

Enabled for Markets

(IND-VELO, PAK-VELO, PH-GLO, UAE-VELO, IND-GLO)

All Markets

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. The SAV confirmation is valid only for the session duration
  1. the session is considered completed if the user has closed all current tabs related to the site, or the browser
  1. The site admin is able to manage expiration time of the SAV confirmation in BO
  1. So, for example, if a user has a tab open and we set the SAV  confirmation lifetime to 3 hours, then after 3 hours the popup will be displayed again.
  1. An authorized user marked "Age Confirmed" should never seec the SAV' pop-up when opening the site.
  2. When using multiple tabs, soft-age verification popup will appear on only currently active tab
  1. If the user has confirmed his/her age on the active tab, switching to another Velo tab will not cause the popup to be shown
  2. If the user has not confirmed his/her age on the active tab, but switched to another tab of the site, the popup will also appear there.

CONFIGURATION REQUIREMENTS:

  • Stores > Configuration > Customers > Age verification > Soft Age verification > Verification lifetime = [X] h
    setting should be created in BO

  1. MAIN MENU  (APPROVED)

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT020

I want to be able to see consistent category navigation throughout the site

MAIN MENU BEHAVIOR:

  • Website admin will be able to manage the category tree in admin panel
  • User will be able to:
  • open menu off-canvas by clicking on the menu icon in header, page behind off-canvas will have dark overlay
  • scroll menu in case q-ty of items is overflowing the height of the screen, cross icon should remain visible upon scrolling
  • click on category link:
  • If category does not have sub-categories
  • there won’t be a chevron on the right side, indicating that there is no next level, upon click user will go to PRODUCT LISTING PAGE of this category
  • user will be redirected directly to the corresponding product listing page, off-canvas menu will be closed during redirection.
  • If category have a sub-category
  • there will be a chevron on the right side, indicating that there is one more category level
  • user will see the second level categories, off-canvas will remain opened, no page reload should occur.
  • if user will click again on the parent category name, the list of child categories will be hidden
  • Click on CMS pages names
  • upon click user will be redirected to a mapped target URL
  • CMS page names and target URLs will be hardcoded
  • List of required CMS page names and URLs should be provided in CONTENT CHECK-LIST
  • close menu using cross icon or clicking on the area outside the main menu (this action will only close the menu, but not perform any action supposed for the element on the page)

DESIGN

MOBILE

DESKTOP

  1. [PHASE II] [BAT-II-0144] LUFT - UI/UX REFRESH ALIGN WITH GLOBAL GUIDELINES - MAIN MENU UPDATES

FEATURE HIGHLIGHTS:

AREAS

SUMMARY

Is this a new Feature or a Change of existing Feature?

Change

What is the Business Need behind this Feature implementation?

Align with Global Guidelines design

Is this feature applied to all resolutions?

Yes

Does this Feature require change in the admin panel?

Yes, Ewave Main Menu module

Are there any dependencies with other Features?

MAIN MENU (APPROVED) will be deprecated

Are there any dependencies with Integrations or 3rd party systems?

No

Applicable for both logged in and guest users?

Yes

Is this Feature market specific?

No, applied to all brands and markets

MODULES TO SUPPORT THIS FEATURE:

  • Ewave Main Menu module is to be installed and leveraged to support menu items configuration in admin panel per website level scope

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS IN ADMIN PANEL:

  • admin is able to create a menu item and specify a category, custom link or CMS block for it
  • admin is able to configure the visibility of an item (specify which storefront the menu item should be visible to)
  • admin able to build menu hierarchy (each menu item can have one parent menu item)
  • admin is able to manage position of the menu items
  • admin able to disable menu item, if menu item has a child item, it will be also disabled
  • admin able to delete menu item, if menu item has a child item, it will be disabled
  • admin is able to specify an icon for the menu item

  1. MAIN MENU MOBILE

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS ON STOREFRONT:

  • open menu off-canvas by clicking on the menu icon in header, page behind off-canvas will have dark overlay and not scrollable
  • scroll menu in case q-ty of items is overflowing the height of the screen, cross icon should remain visible upon scrolling
  • click on text-link:
  • If text-link does not have sub-items:
  • there won’t be a plus on the right side, indicating that there is no next level, upon click a user will go to the target URL of the item, off-canvas menu will be closed during redirection.
  • If text-link has a sub-items:
  • there will be a plus on the right side, indicating that there is one more level
  • upon click user will see the second level items, off-canvas will remain opened, no page reload should occur.
  • if user will click again on the parent text-link, the list of child items will be hidden
  • close menu using cross icon or clicking on the area outside the main menu (this action will only close the menu, but not perform any action supposed for the element on the page)

BLOCK ELEMENTS:

Header:

  • same elements’ behavior as described in [PHASE II] [BAT-II-0144] LUFT - UI/UX REFRESH ALIGN WITH GLOBAL GUIDELINES - HEADER UPDATES
  • click on any icon will close Main menu

Main Menu items:

  • 1st level text-link icon
  • 1st level text-link name
  • minus icon, should be displayed as a plus when accordion is closed
  • accordion with 2nd level items related to the 1st level item, with icon and name of the 2nd level text-link
  • 1st level text-link target URL
  • 1st level item with no child items assigned

  • non manageable menu item
  • upon click will open an accordion with all available settings below

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  • default Magento search functionality will be used
  • admin will be able to set up misspelled words and synonyms using default Magento functionality
  • admin will be able to configure searchable attributes to products via the Magento backend
  • user will be able to initiate search by clicking on search search icon/search input field
  • user will be able to close search by clicking anywhere outside of the search pop-up

  1. SEARCH POP-UP

  1. INITIAL STATE

  • user will see this state when no search query was provided or the provided search query is less than required amount of symbols (3 symbols)
  • depending on the previous search history, user will see:
  • blank pop-up with no details if there is no data to display
  • pop-up that will show one or both if there is data to display:
  • previous search queries, if there are any
  • previously viewed products, if there are any

POP-UP ELEMENTS:

Search input field:

  • placeholder text, not manageable
  • will be replaced with search query once user starts to type in

Previous search queries:

  • block together with the title won’t be displayed if there are no previous searches
  • block title will be not manageable
  • previous search queries storage and functionality will work as per current behavior

Previously viewed products::

  • block together with the title won’t be displayed if there are no previous searches
  • block title will be not manageable
  • previously viewed products storage and functionality will work as per current behavior

VISUAL EXAMPLES:

There are no VE.

Assumption: No mockups to be provided, development team to work directly from brand guidelines with an agreed set of changes to be described and defined without any visual source of requirements

  1. FILTERING (DESKTOP/MOBILE)

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  1. Management Filter attributes will be via CMS (Desktop and Mobile).
  2. Desktop
  1. The Filter block will be displayed on the left side of PLP.
  2. If there is at least one filter with options applicable, the Filter block will be displayed.
  3. Filterable attribute name will be a title of the block.
  4. The Filter sub-sections will be displayed as accordions.
  1. Clicking on "+" will expand the accordion;
  2. Clicking “-" will hide the accordion.
  3. ‘+More’  if quantity of options exceed 4 items
  • Once  '+More' is clicked, all options will be displayed
  1.  List of supported options:
  1. Single-select links;
  1. Selection behavior.
  1. Selected value is highlighted;
  2.  If any filter is  applied, an additional block with applied filters will be displayed.
  • each selected option will be displayed as a separate tag;
  • the corresponding Filter attribute in the Filter section will disappear till the user closes the tag.
  • Each tag will be displayed with  different color from the background
  • The tag  contains Filter title and selected value as: [Filter title]: [Selected value].
  • Each tag has a ‘remove’ icon (cross). Upon click, the user will be able to remove this option from applied filters;
  • Sort order will be manageable in CMS
  1. The tool-tip with the text will appear after hovering the text and color swatches. The text will correspond to the selected values.
  2. “Clear All’ button  will be displayed in the upper right corner of the Filter block if there is at least 1 filter applied.
  1. Upon click "Clear all"  - all selected options will be removed/unselected, the Clear all option will disappear.
  1. The page content will be reloaded after the filter is applied.

  1. Mobile
  1. Filter button
  1. ‘Filter’ button will be shown on PLP and SEARCH RESULTS PAGE (WIP).
  • Button ‘Filter’ is  sticky and placed on the bottom of the page (over the products grid)
  • When the User scrolls down the page and the Footer is shown, then the button will be "fixed" above the Footer.
  1. If filtering options are already defined/set for attribute  it will be mirrored into the brackets on the button.
  • Counter will show how many attributes are used. Counter will be displayed in a different colour then the button title.
  1. When the user clicks the button, then 1-level filtering menu (popup) will be shown.
  2. When the user clicks the filtering option on 1-level filtering pop-up, then  the 2-level popup will be displayed.
  3. All available filtering options will be presented on the 2-level popup.
  1.  1-level filtering popup
  1. The popup is  shown in two cases:
  •  User clicks on "Filter" button on PLP or SEARCH RESULTS PAGE (WIP)
  • User clicks on "Back" button on 2-level filtering popup
  1. The popup has next elements:
  • TopBar
  1. There are Title, Close button (cross) and Clear button in the Topbar
  2. Title text is  Filter
  3. If User clicks ‘Close’ button  - the popup will be closed. The User will  see target PLP or Search results page. All defined filters will be mirrored in the Filter button in parentheses and will be  performed on the page.
  4.  If the user clicks ‘Clear’ button -  all active/selected filters will be reset. Thet user will see the pop-up in its initial state. "Clear" button will be visible, even if no filters are applied.
  1. Filter list section
  • Filter list section should show all available filtering attributes/items.
  • Every filtering attribute is  placed on its own sub-section. If user clicks the sub-section  - then 2-level filtering menu (popup) is shown
  • Supported filter options:
  1.  single select
  1. ‘Show results’ button
  • 'Show results' button is sticky and always available on the bottom of the popup. If the User clicks  the button - popup will be closed. The user will  see target PLP (or search results page). All defined filters will be mirrored in the Filter button in parentheses and will be  performed on the page.
  1. 2-level filtering popup
  1. The popup will be shown after User clicks on filtering attribute/item on the 1-level filtering popup
  2.  The popup should have next elements:
  • TopBar
  1. There are Title, Back button and Clear button in the Topbar
  2. The label will correspond the selected filter attribute/item
  3. If User clicks the ‘Back’ button - the popup will be closed. User will see 1-level filtering popup.
  4. If User clicks the ‘Clear’ button - t all active/selected options will be reset. The user will see popup in its initial state.
  5.  If the user clicks ‘Clear’ button -  all active/selected filters will be reset. Thet user will see the pop-up in its initial state. "Clear" button will be visible, even if no filters are applied
  •  Options list
  1. Filter options list section should show all available items
  2. Next filter option types should be supported:
  1.  single select
  • Apply button
  1. Apply button is sticky and always available on the bottom of the popup. If User clicks the button - popup will be closed. 1-level filtering popup will be shown, popup content will match selected values. All defined/selected options will be mirrored and performed.
  2. Selected option(s)will be applied/performed  after clicking the "Apply" button.
  3. Vertical scroll bar will be available in case, when the options list section is too large.

VISUAL EXAMPLES:

There are no VE.

Assumption: No mockups to be provided, development team to work directly from brand guidelines with an agreed set of changes to be described and defined without any visual source of requirements

  1. SORTING

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  1. Managing  Sorting option will be via CMS.
  2. Mobile:
  1. "Sort by" button will be shown on PLP.
  1. Button will be sticky and placed on the bottom of the page (over the products grid).
  2. When a user scrolls down the page and the Footer is shown, then the button should be "fixed" above the Footer.
  3. If the sorting attribute is defined it will be reflected on the button. Information about the selected sort attribute should be displayed under the [Sort by] text on the button. This information will be displayed in different colour then button title.
  4. If a user clicks the button - [Sort by] pop-up is opened.

  1. “Sort by” pop-up contains the following components:
  1. Top-Bar.
  • There are ‘Close’ button, Title and ‘Clear’ button in the TopBar
  1. When a user clicks the ”Close” button they are redirected to the PLP page. Defined sorting option will be mirrored in the ‘Sort by’ button and performed for  the page.
  2. Title “Sort by”.
  3. When a user clicks the “Clear’’ button the [Sort by] pop-up is displayed according to default state
  1. Section for choosing the sorting attribute
  • This section contains the list of sorting options which are provided via CMS.
  • Only one sorting attribute will be selected at once.
  • Default sorting attribute depends on data which is provided byCMS: If nothing is provided by CMS, there are no pre-selected attribute on the pop-up. If admin sets default sorting attribute then it is displayed on the pop-up in the selected state.
  • Descending order is used for sort order.
  • Sorting is applied right after the sorting attribute was selected.
  1. Desktop. 
  1. Logic is the same as for Mobile Version (see above) accept some differences:
  1. "Sort by"  dropdown will be shown on the top of the PLP page on the right side. The sorting attribute should be selected via dropdown.
  • Text label [Sort By:]
  • Text field.
  1. The default sorting attribute will be displayed in the field (if any exists)
  2. If there is no default sorting attribute , an empty field will be displayed .
  •   Dropdown to select the sorting attribute.
  1. When a user clicks the dropdown: it is expanded, they will be able to select the sorting attribute.
  2. The drop-down will be collapsed after the user selects the attribute AND the selected value will be displayed in the text field.
  3. Products on the PLP are displayed according to the selected sorting attribute.

VISUAL EXAMPLES:

There is no VE.

Assumption: No mockups to be provided, development team to work directly from brand guidelines with an agreed set of changes to be described and defined without any visual source of requirements

  2. SEARCH POP-UP AND SEARCH RESULTS PAGE (APPROVED)

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT047

I want to use default Magento search on the website

BAT048

I want to be able to configure searchable attributes to products via the Magento backend

  1. SEARCH POP-UP

POP-UP ELEMENTS:

  1. Search popup will be shown when a user clicks the Search icon on the Header.
  2. There are 3 states for the popup - "initial", "search results", "no results".
  1. ‘initial’ state - before applying search process and receiving search results
  2. ‘search results’ state - after applying search process, when there are any results which correspond to the request
  3. ‘no results’ state - after applying search process, when there are no results matching the request
  1. Page elements:
  1. TopBar.
  1. There are  ‘Close’ button, Search request input field, search button (magnified into the field) and Title in the TopBr
  • If User clicks the ‘Close’ button - the popup will be closed. Any changes/actions will not be performed. A user will see the current/actual page.
  • Search request input field has 2 states: default and active (highlighted). The field will get an active state when the cursor is set in the field.
  • Search button (as a loupe icon) is disabled until at least one symbol is entered to the search request input field. After clicking the button the search process is initiated according to the current request.
  1. Recent Searches block (optional).
  1. The block will be shown only on "initial" state on Search pop-up in case at least one search request has been processed during current user’s session.
  2. There are Title and list of items (recently searched).
  •  The title is "Recent Searches".
  • The list of items will contain not more than 5 lines (5 recently searched items.
  1. The items in the list will be ordered by the recency (the latest element will be placed on the top)..
  2. If a user clicks some item in the list, the Search request input field will be populated with the corresponding request. The user will have to click on the Search button in order to perform the search.
  1. Related Products block
  1. This block is shown in ‘search results’ state of Search pop-up
  2.  There are  Title, Product Tiles, ‘Show more’ button in the Related Products block.
  • Title is “Related Products’
  • 2 product tiles will be displayed as maximum.
  • "Show more" option will be shown in case when more than 2 products are related to the current search request.
  1. When a user clicks the "Show More" button the Product Search Results page will be shown.
  1. "No results" popup state:
  1. Information message for Related Product section will be “Sorry, no products available for current options”.

  1. Vertical scroll bar will be available in case of large content on the popup.

VISUAL EXAMPLES:

There are no VE.

Assumption: No mockups to be provided, development team to work directly from brand guidelines with an agreed set of changes to be described and defined without any visual source of requirements

  1. SEARCH RESULTS PAGE

PAGE ELEMENTS:

  1. Product search results page will be shown when the user clicks the "Show More" button on the Search popup.
  2. All products which are related to the current search request will be shown on the page.
  3. TopBar
  1. There are Back icon, Title in the TopBar
  1. Upon clicking on the button User will be redirected to the previously visited page. When destination is not defined, then User should be redirected to Homepage.
  2. Text for the Title will be "YY RESULTS FOR XXXX", where YY is a number of products on PLP and XXXX is the current search request. If the request is too long - it will be cropped and ended with dots.
  1. Product tiles grid will be the same as described in Product Grid and will show search results.
  2. Filters
  1. [mobile] Upon click ‘Filter’ button  Filter Blocks will be opened.
  2. [desktop] Filter block will be displayed on the Search results page
  1. Sort by button
  1. [mobile] Upon click ‘Sort by’ button Sort pop-up will be displayed
  2. [desktop] Sort by field will be displayed on the Search results page.
  1. Vertical scroll bar will be available in case, when the page is too large.

VISUAL EXAMPLES:

There are no VE.

Assumption: No mockups to be provided, development team to work directly from brand guidelines with an agreed set of changes to be described and defined without any visual source of requirements

will be deprecated

Yes

Market or Core?

Core

(VELO-ID, VELO-PAK, VELO-UAE, GLO-PH, GLO-ID, Vuse)

All

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  1. Breadcrumbs will be displayed on the top of PDP and below the Header.
  2. Breadcrumbs will contain the “Home” item, parent categorie’s items which product is assigned under and current Product page item
  1. The parent categories’ items included will depend on where the user access the PDP from
  2. Example: Home / Pilih Varian / 3 Tropic Mix Bundle;  if access PDP from Pilih Varian product listing page
  3. Example: Home / Promo Bundle / 3 Tropic Mix Bundle;  if access PDP from Promo Bundle product listing page
  4. Example: Home / 3 Tropic Mix Bundle; if access PDP from Homepage
  5. If there are multiple levels of categories, e.g. the product is assigned under a Lv2 category, both Lv1 and Lv2 category item will be included in Breadcrumbs
  1. Upon click “Home”, ther user will be redirected to Homepage
  2. All parent categories will be clickable, upon clicking a user will be redirected to the corresponding category product listing page.
  3. All items are displayed in the breadcrumbs.  No "Back icon" is displayed.
  4. [MOBILE] Breadcrumb will be displayed in two rows if all items cannot display in full in one row.

VISUAL EXAMPLES:

DESKTOP

MOBILE

Display in two rows when can’t display in full in one row

  1. PRODUCT IMAGE GALLERY BLOCK

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • [DESKTOP] Image navigation block
  • If a product has only one image (video) assigned or no images (video), this block won’t be displayed.
  • if more than 1 image (video)  assigned, navigation with product image thumbnails will appear on the left side of the  currently selected product image
  • quantity of thumbnails will be corresponding to the quantity images (videos) assigned to the currently selected product
  • thumbnail, corresponding to the currently selected image (video), will be highlighted with the  blue frame
  • clicking on thumbnail, like thumbnail, will change the  currently selected product image (video) to the corresponding to the thumbnail image
  •  If the height of the thumbnails line  is greater than Product Gallery section the thumbnails will be scrolled
  • Currently selected product image block
  • If no images assigned - > a placeholder image should be displayed in this block, styling as per 1 image assigned case. The placeholder image can be manageable via admin
  • If one image is assigned -> this single image should be displayed in this block, no additional elements will appear.
  • If more than 1 image is assigned, then images should be organized in a carousel.
  • placeholder image is to be confirmed in IMAGE PLACEHOLDER section
  • if there is an image/images assigned
  • user will be able to zoom in the product image by clicking on it or touching (on mobile)
  • Swiping a zoomed image will  affect focus changing
  • images work as per default Magento logic
  • if there is more than one image assigned
  • LEFT arrow and RIGHT arrow will be displayed,
  • image carousel will not be looped
  • user will be able to click on arrows to navigate between images, or use swipe gestures on mobile
  • the scroll bar will be displayed in the bottom, showing the current progress in the image carousel
  • If there is assigned video to the Product, the video will be displayed in the Product gallery with the option to "Play"
  • the image will be changes in accordance with the selected Product configuration option: swatches (if the corresponding images exist)

BLOCK ELEMENTS:

  1. [DESKTOP] Image navigation block
  1. currently selected thumbnail
  2. thumbnail
  1. Currently selected product image
  1. product image
  2. LEFT arrow
  3. RIGHT arrow
  4. scroll bar

  1. PRODUCT SUMMARY BLOCK

BLOCK ELEMENTS:

  1. Product name
  • If the product name is too long to fit in one line, the product name will go to the line below
  1. Product SKU
  1. Product price
  • default Magento behavior will be applied
  • supported price see in WEBSITE PRICE FORMAT (PENDING)
  • if discounted the price will be displayed as "striked-out"in 2 lines
  • If there is a minimal price, it should be displayed like "as low as". The “as low as “ will be displayed above the price
  1. Product Stock status
  • default Magento logic will be applied to show stock status
  • Options: In Stock, Out of Stock
  1. Product configuration option: swatches
  • will be displayed for configurable products
  • Title: Strength
  • The placeholder [Please select] will be displayed if there is no selected attribute.
  1. If some attribute was selected, the placeholder will be changed to the corresponding attribute name.
  • [desktop] If the user moves the cursor to the attribute, the tool-tip will appear with the corresponding attribute name
  • Product configuration block behavior:
  1. When the page is loaded, no option is pre-selected by default. User will need to select required options in swatches.
  2. User will be able to  select only one option
  3. If an option is out of stock, it will still be displayed in the list of swatches, but  the name of the option will be light-gray and strike-out and user won’t be able to select it.
  4. When User selects target variant  - it will  be mirrored on the page:
  • selected option (swatch)   will be highlighted with blue frame
  • configuration block  title will show related variant name
  • product image will be updated (target image will be shown in Product images/gallery block if exists)
  1. “Quantity” input field 
  • Quantity stepper will be shown below the Configuration block (for configurable product) or below the main product information block (for simple products).
  • Quantity stepper will not be shown in case product is not available for sale (out of stock)  
  • Initial state of the  stepper counter  is "1"
  • Upon click on plus or minus the quantity will be increased/decreased by 1 (won’t be manageable)
  • It will not be possible to set 0 value
  • [mobile] The user is able to change quantity via arrows in the block.  It should not be possible to use input field and keyboard for quantity changing.
  • [desktop] The user is able to change quantity via arrows and via keyboard.
  1. ‘Add to Cart’ button
  • "Add To Cart" will  be active by default for Simple products
  •  "Add to cart" button will be disabled:
  1.  for "Out of stock" products
  2. if the price for the product is not defined
  3. when product is not available for sale (f.e. required options are not selected for configurable product)
  • Upon click on active "Add To Cart" button:
  1. product(s) will be added to the cart
  2. user will  stay at the same PDP
  3. After the  product(s) were successfully added, the user will see a message with text: ‘You added [product name] to your shopping cart’.
  1. [mobile] Floating ‘Add to Cart’ block shown in the bottom of the PDP
  • Floating block is presented as aggregation of:
  1. "Add To Cart" button
  2. Price: Price is  shown, calculated and updated according to page state, quantity value and product configuration.

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  •  A ‘PDP Color code’ attribute should be added in the admin panel
  • Input type - Visual swatch
  • The site admin will be able to add and manage colors in the attribute through the BO
  • The site admin will be able to select a relevant 'color code' value
  • The color of the PDP elements will change depending on the selected product Color code value.
  • The ‘Strength’ attribute should be changed from ‘Visual swatch’ type to the ‘Text swatch’ type
  • necessary in order to achieve the desired hover effect recommended in the guideline
  • An additional attribute "Subtitle" should be created in the admin panel
  • the attribute will be displayed under the product name and give users important additional information about the product
  • An additional ‘product-detail-component-delivery-banner’ Luft container should be created
  • The container is allow displaying CMS banners on the PDP
  •  A CMS  banner is assigned at the store level (all products of a particular store will display the same banner)
  • [mobile] The block with limited amount of reviews should be displayed directly on the detail page

PAGE ELEMENTS CHANGES

DESIGN

  1. ‘Brand’ attribute
  • The site admin will be able to assign and manage brand for each product
  • If no brand is specified, the line will be hidden
  • Text color does not change
  • Always in capital letters, according to the guidelines
  1. Product name
  • Always in capital letters, according to the guidelines
  • Depending on the selected Color code, the color of the product name will be changed
  • The SKU is not displayed
  1. Product subtitle
  •  An additional attribute will be created in the admin panel
  • Displayed under the title
  • If no Subtitle is specified, the line will be hidden

  1. Short description
  • [mobile] is displayed below the product image
  • [desktop] is displayed below the product subtitle
  1. Product swatches
  • should be styled according to global guidelines
  • displayed as two lines: value, dots
  • the number of dots will be equivalent to the number of options (swatches) available for the configurable product
  • the fullness of the dots will depend on the position of the option in the attribute option list
    (the first swatch (option) will have one filled dot, the second - twбo the last one - all the dots filled)
  • the site admin will be able to change the option order in the attribute through the admin panel
  1. Price
  • Should be in bold
  • The discounted price style will remain the same as it is now (the black price is crossed out, the price is written in red on the right), but only in bold.

  1. CTA buttons
  • ‘Cart’ should be replaced with ‘Basket’
  • the color of the buttons does not depend on the product color code
  • [desktop] if the width of the screen allows the buttons should be placed horizontally
  1. Delivery promo banner
  • displayed on the page via 'product-detail-component-delivery-banner' container
  • if the admin has not filled the container, it will not be displayed on the PDP
  • One and the same banner for all store products

  1. All product information other than Reviews should be excluded from the PDP.

  1. Product rating bar should be displayed at the top of the page
  • The styling is aligned with the global design
  • when user clicks on "reviews", the page is scrolled down to the desired section

  1. The Reviews block
  • Styling as per mockups
  • [mobile] The most recent 3 reviews are displayed directly on the product details page
  • Reviews larger than three lines are cropped with ellipsis
  • by clicking on a review, it will be expanded in its entirety. On second click - collapsed

  • [desktop] Initially only the last 5 reviews will be displayed on the product details page
  • Reviews larger than four lines are cropped with ellipsis
  • A user will be able to view the full review by clicking the appropriate link under the post
  • at the bottom of the block there will be a "Read all reviews" button
  • [mobile] upon click user will go to the Reviews tab (as is)
  • [deskpot] when clicked, all reviews will be expanded and loaded through an infinite scrolling feature
  • All other functionality remains in accordance with [PHASE ll] [BAT-II-0022] PRODUCT RATING AND REVIEW
  1. Recommended products carousel
    should be added to the page
  • The site admin will be able to manage "Recommended products" for each product in the "Up-Sell Products" section via BO
  • The element behavior corresponds to the standard site carousels:
    PRODUCT CAROUSELS (DESKTOP)
    PRODUCT CAROUSELS (MOBILE)

  1. Product image should take the whole block space
  2. Image gallery navigation arrows styling is aligned with the global design
  3. [Desktop] thumbnails are located at the bottom of the image
  • No thumbnails for mobile

  1.  input field (is mandatory).

  1. input field (is mandatory)

  3. Upon successful validation a user will be redirected to My Account navigation page.
  1. When a user initiates a login procedure from Checkout, then we will show the Сart page (with corresponding tab in active state) after successful validation.
  2. The success message “You have successfully logged in” will be shown.

  1. If email validation is failed then the Email Address input field will be shown in error-state.
  1. "Please enter a valid email address." text-message will be used .
  2. Password input field will appear in default state.
  1. If password validation is failed then the error message will be shown on the page.  
  1. Password input field will appear in default state.

  2. Upon clicking the link the "Forgot Password" page will be opened.
  1. "Create An Account" block will be shown under "Forgot Your Password?" text link.

  1. [BAT-005-CR] 1-2-1 AGENT REFERRAL CODE ATTRIBUTION

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • Users will have an ability to enter a Referral code during registration.
  • a text field, optional, no validation required
  • Storefront label: Kode Referensi, Default label: Referral Code, Attribute code: referral
  • users will be able to add/update/delete data in this text field before registration form is submitted
  • Admin will have an ability to add Referral code when creating a new Customer via admin panel.
  • Admin will have an ability to read/update/delete data in this text field in a Customer account via admin panel.
  • System will save the value of the “Referral code” on Customer entity level, after a Registration form is successfully submitted from storefront.

ASSUMPTIONS AND CONSTRAINTS:

  • Codes will be generated and distributed outside of the Magento admin panel and storefront.
  • No integration with a third party system is required for MVP scope.
  • No custom reporting interface on the Magento admin panel.
  • Order and fulfilment will be handled off-line by 1-2-1 agents, website won’t be used for order placement and fulfilment.
  • Users won’t be able to read/update/delete data submitted in this text field after Registration.

  2. When a logged-in user access ACCOUNT INFORMATION page, try to edit and click ‘Save Changes’ button on the page, system will check if the phone number already exists in the system or not, if yes, an error message will be displayed, telling user that this phone number already exists in the system and can not be saved.   • Google

  • user will see a success message with the following text:
  • “Anda telah berhasil masuk” (IND)
  • “You have successfully logged in” (PK, PH)

  • once authorization is completed, a success message with the following text will be displayed:
  • Akun <Nama Jaringan Sosial> Anda sekarang terhubung ke akun pengguna baru Anda di toko kami. (IND)
  • Your <Social Network name> account is now connected to your new user account at our store. (PK, PH)
  • user will be logged in
  • If email address is absent in the Social Network data, the following message will be displayed:
  • Sayangnya, kami tidak dapat mendaftarkan Anda segera karena tidak ada email yang diberikan oleh <nama_jejaring_sosial>. Silakan, coba cara lain untuk mendaftar. (IND)
  • Unfortunately, we were not able to register you as soon as there's no email provided by <social_network_name>. Please, try another way to register. (PK)
  • If First Name/Last Name is absent in the Social Network data, the following message will be displayed:
  • Sayangnya, kami tidak dapat mendaftarkan Anda segera setelah kami tidak dapat mengambil <nama_jaringan_sosial> nama depan atau belakang Anda. (IND)
  • Unfortunately, we were not able to register you as soon as we could not retrieve your <social_network_name> first or last name. (PK)
  • If there is an account with the email address received from Social Network:
  • the existing account will be connected with the Social Network account and user will be able to log in next time without password using Social Network login button
  • On Security and Login page in My Account, logged in user will be able to link/unlink a Social Network account

  • When User clicks on the social login button and we get the email address from the social network, if there is no account previously linked or created with the same email address, the following will happen;
  • user will be redirected to the Social Login Registration page
  • all the data (email, first name and last name) received from Social Network will be pre-filled on the page
  • all the customer profile attributes will be the same as for Registration page with same validation requirements
  • Terms and Conditions consent (checkbox) will be received on this page as well
  • NO password input field will be displayed for the Social Login Registration page
  • After all validations passed, user account will be registered and created in the database
  • If validation is not passed for at least one field or checkbox, user account will not be created, user will stay on the same page and error message near the corresponding field will be displayed

Is this feature applied to all resolutions?

Yes

Yes

No

No

No (for Logged in  users only)

Yes (Philipine market only)

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

GPH_US041-1

As a user, I want to be able to subscribe newsletter from registration page

GPH_US041-2

As a user, I want to see newsletter subscription and “consent to use data” checkbox are pre-ticked when I open the registration page

GPH_US041-3

As a user, I want to be able to manage my marketing preferences (newsletter subscription, content to use data) in My account page

GPH_US041-4

As a system admin, I want to be able to update the content on marketing preferences page

PAGE ELEMENTS:

  1. Registration page

Leverage current Registration Page feature but make the following updates:

  • Update the text “Terms & Conditions”  to “I agree to the processing of my personal data in accordance with the Terms of Use of the Site , Consent to the processing of personal data, I fully and unconditionally accept them. I also agree to the processing of my personal data to confirm my age”
  • ‘Terms of Use of the Site’ link leads to the Terms of Use page
  • ‘Consent to the processing of personal data’ - to the Privacy Policy page
  • Update the text “I would like to receive an exclusive offer updates from GLO” to “Consent to Use Data”
  • Add a “Newsletter” subscription option under “Consent to use data” attribute
  • Checkbox, optional field
  • Name displayed in storefront is: Newsletter
  • Magento OOTB newsletter subscription feature will be leveraged
  • Pre-tick “Newsletter” and “Consent to use data” “...receive updates from GLO” checkbox on the page, but allow users to untick them.
  • If a user checks 'I would like to receive updates from glo' for registration, the ‘eMail Newsletter’ and ‘Contact by Mobile Phone' checkboxes in the marketing preference page will be checked.
  • Magento OOTB newsletter feature will be leveraged for ‘eMail Newsletter”
  • ‘Consent’ attribute will be leveraged for ‘Contact by Mobile Phone’’
  1. My Account page
  • The Marketing preferences page will be opened after user clicks the Marketing Preferences section in the My Account navigation menu
  • Page elements [Desktop] has the same elements, instead of Back icon,  via section:
  1. TopBar is shown on the top of the page. It has 2 elements: [mobile] Back-button and Title
  • [mobile] Back icon upon click on the  button, user should be redirected to previous page
  • Title is 'MARKETING PREFERENCES'
  1. Content / Text except for ‘eMail Newsletter’ and ‘Contact by Mobile Phone’  options can be managed from admin panel
  2. eMail Newsletter
  • When the checkbox is checked -  the user will receive newsletters.
  • When the checkbox is unchecked - the user cancels subscription for newsletters.​
  • Default state is 'unchecked', except the following case:
    When a guest user     subscribed for a newsletter by checking ‘'I would like to receive updates from glo' for registration’ during registration and logged in later with the same email, they will see the option 'Newsletter' checkbox in state with 'checked' on marketing preferences page
  • If the option subscription to ‘Newsletter' is disabled in the admin panel the “eMail Newsletter” option will not be displayed in storefront (including on registration page and marketing preferences page), in marketing preferences page. Content that is managed by CMS blocks will need to be disabled by admin manually.
  1. Contact by Mobile Phone
  • when the checkbox is checked - the user accepts their data to be used for business purposes.
  • when the checkbox is unchecked - the user disagrees with their data to be used for business purposes.
  • Default state is 'unchecked' unless user check ‘'I would like to receive updates from glo' for registration’ when registration
  • “Consent to Use Data’ in My Account page will be removed as it will be displayed on marketing preferences page
  1. Save button
  • Clicking on Save button, the changes that the user makes on the marketing preference page will be saved to user’s profile
  1. Email Notifications
  • User will be able to receive a ‘Subscription” email if user subscribe newsletter successfully
  • User will be able to receive a ‘Unsubscription” email if user unsubscribe newsletter successfully

VISUAL EXAMPLES:

MOBILE

DESKTOP

  1. ACCOUNT NEWSLETTER SUBSCRIPTION PAGE

PAGE ELEMENTS:

  • The page will be opened after clicking the Newsletter section in the My Account navigation menu
  • Page elements [Desktop] has the same elements, instead of Back icon,  via section:
  • TopBar is shown on the top of the page. It has 2 elements: [mobile] Back-button and Title
  • [mobile] Back icon upon click on the  button, user should be redirected to previous page
  • Title is 'Newsletter'
  •   'General subscription' toggle.
  • When toggle is set in 'on' -  the user will receive newsletters.
  • When toggle is set in 'off' - the user cancels subscription for newsletters.​
  • Default state is 'off', except the following case: when a guest user subscribed for a newsletter and logged in later with the same email they will see the option 'Newsletter' in state 'On' in My Account Navigation menu.
  • If the option 'Subscription to the newsletter' is disabled in a back-office the corresponding tab will not be displayed in My Account Navigation menu.

BAT-II-0306-1

As a user, I want to see ‘consent to data use’ checkbox without pre-ticked in the registration page same as on Velo Indo and PK sites

BAT-II-0306-2

As a user, I want to see ‘consent to data use’ checkbox in my Account Information page same as on Velo Indo and PK sites

As a user, I won’t see ‘Marketing Preferences’ page in my account

As a system, I want Marketing preferences feature to be excluded in Vuse MY website

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  3. The ‘Consent to data use’ checkbox can’t be turned on or off from admin panel
  4. This model is suitable for further integration with SF CRM as on Velo Indo site.
  1. After the modification of the code, Marketing Preferences feature which was built on top of default magento newsletter model will be removed from Vuse MY website
  1. MARKETING PREFERENCES page and the associated features as described [GPH-US041] MARKETING PREFERENCES won’t be shown in user’s my account page
  2. The enablement or disablement of the default magento newsletter feature from the admin panel won’t be reflected in registration and user’s account pages in the storefront

USER STORY

BAT-II-0217-US1

As a system, I want a new password policy to be applied.

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. 2FA should be enabled for the Privileged (admin) accounts
  2. The actions of Privileged (admin)  users must be logged:
  1. All successful and unsuccessful login attempts
  2. All logoffs
  3. Actions performed in the back office (Modifications to system settings, user accounts/privileges, other actions to modify back office entities)

NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Privileged (Admin) Accounts must have a minimum password length of 12 characters
  2. End user accounts must have a minimum password length of 8 characters;
  3. Password complexity must be enforced for all user passwords and should be based on a combination of uppercase, lowercase and digits and if available special characters
  1. The site admin can manage requirements for the customer password in:
    BO > Store > Configurations > Customer configuration > Password options >
  • Number of Required Character Classes
  • Minimum Password Length
  1. Requirements for the privileged (admin) accounts will be hardcoded
  1. 2FA should be enabled for privileged accounts logins
  2. All stored passwords must be hashed (SHA256) and salted (32 bits or more).

  1. CUSTOMER PASSWORDS UPDATE

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. New customer attribute "password updated" is to be added
  2. When a user without the "Password updated" checkbox logs in, they should be redirected to the Reset Password page.
  1. when trying to go to another page of the site through the menu, banners, or a direct link, the user should still be redirected to the Reset password page
  1. On the Reset Password page, the user should see an info block about why they ended up here and what conditions the new password must meet.
  2. After successfully changing the password, the user should be flagged as "Password updated = Yes"
  3. All newly registered users should get the "Password updated = Yes" flag automatically.

NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. The info block text: TBC

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0217-US3

As a system, I want to keep a log of the actions of customers.

BAT-II-0217-US4

As a site admin, I want be able to see and export the customer  action log

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. The actions of customers must be logged:
  1. All successful and unsuccessful login attempts
  2. All logoffs
  3. ‘Security and Login’ setting changes
  1. A separate table should be created to display logs in the admin panel (similar to the log of admin actions)
  1. The site admin can use filtering and sorting
  2. The admin can export log to CSV file manually
  1. A related cron job should be created
  1. The job should export (archive) data on user actions for the period to a CSV file
  • The site administrator should be able to manage the frequency and lifetime of the archive in the admin panel.
  1. The admin should be able to set the schedule and frequency of archiving in the admin panel
  2. A separate log file should be created for each store.
  3. After export, the log table in the system should be cleared
  4. The administrator should be able to set the storage period for archives in the admin panel
  1. A separate table should be created to display user log archive in the admin panel (similar to the archive of admin actions)
  1. the table should contain a list of available CSV files and the date of their creation
  2. When clicking on the CSV file, the file downloading to the local admin's device should be initiated

NON - FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Archive name must consist of [Date] + ‘-’ + [Website code]:
  1. 2020080819-PK.csv

CONFIGURATION REQUIREMENTS:

  1. User actions should be logged separately for each store.
  1. The market admin should only have access to the records of their local store.
  2. The global admin must have access to the entire action log.
  1. The log table and archive should be available at:
  1. BO > System > Action Logs > Customer Report
  2. BO > System > Action Logs > Customer Actions Archive
  1. Two additional settings is to be created
    BO> Stores > Configuration > System >     Customer Action Log archiving
  1. Log entry lifetime, Days - numeric input field
  2. Log Archiving Frequency - dropdown (daily, weekly)

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0117-US1

As an admin, I want to enable/disable mini-cart per web-site

BAT-II-0117-US2

As an user, I want to see a mini-cart off-canvas each time I add a product to cart or when I click on cart icon in header

 

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Admin should be able to enable/disable mini cart per web-site using configuration in the admin panel
  2. When mini cart is disabled, users will see toast notifications when they add product to cart and will go to Cart page when they click on the cart icon in Header
  3. When mini cart is enabled, users will see mini-cart off-canvas each time they add a product to cart or when they click on cart icon in header
  4. When mini cart is open:
  1. page behind the off-canvas will have dark overlay
  2. page behind the off-canvas won’t be scrollable
  3. upon click anywhere outside of the off-canvas area, mini cart will be closed
  4. blocks #1 and #3 will be sticky and not scrollable
  5. when the amount of products exceeds screen height, scroll will appear on the right side of block #2

OFF-CANVAS ELEMENTS:

  1. Mini Cart header block
  1. -> arrow icon
  1. upon click will close off-canvas
  1. ‘YOUR BASKET’ (EN) / ‘KERANJANG’ (ID)
  1. hardcoded text, not manageable
  1. ‘BASKET TOTAL:’ (EN) / ‘‘KERANJANG TOTAL’ (ID)
  1. hardcoded text, not manageable
  1. amount
  1. dynamic value,
  2. currency format as per web-site
  1. quantity of items
  1. dynamic value
  2. show quantity of SKUs (not SKU x quantity) in  Cart

  1. Mini Cart products
  1. product  
  1. delete icon
  1. upon click user will delete the product from Cart
  2. no additional confirmation to delete product will be displayed
  3. cart total will be recalculated respectively
  1. product thumbnail image
  2. product name
  3. product price (discounted price, if applicable)
  4. product quantity
  1. user will be able to update the quantity
  2. quantity can not be less than 1
  1. variation of the product (if a configurable product)
  2. edit icon (if a configurable product) - refer to ‘Edit a configurable product’ flow below for details
  3. stock status
  1. if a product in cart is out of stock, the global error message will be displayed in the same way as it works on Cart
  1. if there is more than one product added to cart, product tiles will be stacked one under another

Edit a configurable product:

  1. if user clicks on the edit icon the block with the available configurations will be displayed:
  1. currently selected configuration
  • no action upon click
  1. other available configurations, that are not currently selected
  • will be displayed as swatches on PDP
  • upon click on any of the available configurations, it will become current
  • only available configurations are to be displayed (in stock)
  1. ‘update’ button
  • upon click will hide the block with available configurations
  1. edit icon will be hidden while configurations block is open, will be visible again only after user will click update button (c)
  2. if user have this block open for any of the products, he/she is still able to proceed to cart/checkout, currently selected configuration will be used
  3. user can ‘edit’ a few products simultaneously

  1. Mini Cart CTA
  1. ‘PROCEED TO CHECKOUT’ (EN) / ‘BELI LANGSUNG’ (ID)
  1. if there are products in Cart that are out of stock, this button will not be displayed
  2. text will be not manageable  
  3. upon click user will go to checkout page, same as from PDP
  1. ‘VIEW BASKET’ (EN) / ‘LIHAT KERANJANG’ (ID)
  1. text will be not manageable
  2. upon click user will go to cart page

  1. LIST OF ITEMS IN THE  SHOPPING CART PAGE

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • Clicking on the Cart icon at the top of the website, user will be redirected to the shopping cart page, which includes the  information of recently added products.
  •  Page elements:
  • TopBar
  •  TopBar is shown on the top of the page. It has 2 elements: Back button and Title.
  • Upon clicking on the  Back button user should be redirected to previous page
  • Title text is changed dynamically (it depends on cart content). Title format is "XX ITEM(S) $YYYY", where XX is a product counter and YYYY is the subtotal price for all products in the cart.
  • When there are no products in the cart, then title will be "0 ITEM(S)"
  • Functional tabs: Cart, Checkout
  • The tabs are shown below TopBar in case at least 1 product/item is placed in the cart. When there are no any items in the cart - tabs are not displayed
  • For the Shopping Cart page the corresponding tab “Cart” is highlighted with the line in the bottom and another font color..
  • The Checkout tab is available (clickable). If the user clicks the Checkout tab, the corresponding page is opened.
  •  If the guest user is forbidden to proceed to checkout (by setting in CMS), while attempt to open Checkout tab via tab or via Checkout button in SUMMARY BLOCK IN THE SHOPPING CART PAGE (WIP), the Login page will be shown
  • Products listing section
  • [desktop] The section is displayed in the left side behind the Summary block
  • Sticky bottom section
  • Summary block in the Shopping Cart is displayed as a sticky bottom section at  the bottom (in case at least 1 product/item is placed in the cart).
  • [desktop] Summary section will be displayed in the right side behind the product list section
  •  Subtotal block will be sticky in the top  if the user scrolls the cart down
  • CMS block- the сontent can be manageable. The content see in CONTENT CHECK-LIST
  • Products listing section contains sub-sections. Every single item/product is a separate sub-section.
  • The product which is the latest added to cart product will be shown on the top.
  • Every sub-section have next elements:
  • Product Image thumbnail.
  • will correspond to the configurable settings, made by the user.
  • Product Name label
  • will correspond to the configurable settings, made by the user
  • Long names will be placed on two rows.
  • Product Price
  • will correspond to the configurable settings, made by the user
  • [desktop] the price will be displayed in the right side of the product card
  • Configurable attribute options
  • will  be shown only for configurable products.
  • Quantity counter
  • minimal value is 1.
  • Stock status
  • "More options" button (triple-dot icon)
  • After clicking  ¨More options¨ button all page area will  become grayed-out. Three active functional buttons will be shown on the bottom of the page: Edit, Remove, Cancel.
  • [desktop]  Control panel will be opened right near the 3-dot icon
  • Upon click the ‘Edit’ button the EDIT PRODUCT POP-UP FOR SHOPPING CART will be displayed.
  • Upon click the ‘Remove’ button: actions block will be hidden, the modal window ‘Remove item’ will appear
  • There are Title, text message, Cancel button, Remove button in the ‘Remove item’  modal window
  • Title:  ‘Remove item’
  • Text message: 'Are you sure you would like to remove this item
  • from the shopping cart?'
  • Upon click "Cancel" button - modal window will  be closed. The product will remain in the cart. The control panel will be closed.
  • When User clicks "Remove" button:
  •  Modal window will be closed
  •  Target product will  be deleted from the cart.
  • The user will see a success message ‘[product name] has been removed from your shopping cart.’
  • After the user applies ‘Remove’ or ‘Edit’ actions, the page  content will  be reloaded, actual cart content will be shown
  • The preloader should be shown for each product section
  •  If there are any validation errors while data loading, they will be displayed for each product section
  • Upon click the ‘Cancel’ button - functional buttons will be closed. The shopping cart page will be shown in its actual state.
  • When there are no products in the cart,  the Cart page elements are:  
  • TopBar title - "0 ITEM(S)"
  • Functional tabs aren’t shown
  • Products listing section isn’t shown
  • "You have no items in your shopping cart." text is displayed
  • Vertical scroll bar should be available in case the Products listing section is too large.

  1. EDIT PRODUCT POP-UP FOR SHOPPING CART

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • Edit product pop-up is opened  when the User clicks on the ‘Edit’ button in ¨More options¨button on the Shopping Cart page.
  • [desktop] Edit product pop-up will be opened in the right side
  • ¨Edit product¨ menu/popup elements:
  • TopBar
  • TopBar
  • There are 2 elements: ‘Close’ button and Title.
  •  If User clicks ‘Close’ button - the popup will be closed. Any changes will not be saved. User will see the shopping cart page in its actual state.
  • Title text is "Edit Product"
  • Product info
  • Product image thumbnail
  • The image will correspond to the selected product.
  • The image will  be updated dynamically after the user makes changes in the Configuration block.
  •  Product name
  •  The product name will correspond to the selected product.
  • Product SKU
  • Stock status
  • Product Price
  • Actual product price will  be shown.
  •  Price will be dynamic for configurable products. It will depend on selected Attribute's options.
  • Product Configuration block (swatches)
  • Selected option should be mirrored correctly (see details in Product configuration option: swatches for PDP)
  • Quantity stepper
  • will be shown below Product Configuration block (for configurable product) or below Product price block (for simple products).
  • See more details in “Quantity” input field for PDP
  • Functional buttons block
  • will be  placed on bottom of the popup
  • Two active buttons will be shown on the bottom of the page: "Save Changes" and "Cancel"
  • When User clicks the  "Cancel" button - the popup will be closed. Any changes will not be saved and performed.
  • The button "Save Changes" will be disabled till all required attributes are selected.
  •  When User clicks on "Save Changes" button:
  • ¨Edit product¨ menu/popup will be closed
  • The Shopping Cart content will  be reloaded.
  • Target product info will be updated according to new changes.
  • The user will see a message ‘[product name] has been updated in your shopping cart.’
  • Vertical scroll bar should be available in case the informations doesn’t fit size of the pop-up

  1. CHECKOUT PAGE SECTIONS

There is a one-page Checkout flow.

Most fields are available for editing  subsequently. See the rules for each section in the description below.

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • The Checkout page will be opened:
  •  after the User clicks on the active "Checkout" tab  from the Shopping cart page.
  • after User clicks on the "Checkout" button  from the Shopping cart page.
  • The page elements:
  • TopBar
  • There are ‘Back’ button and Title.
  • Upon clicking the Back  button, the  user will see the previously opened page (which was opened before the user has opened Shopping Cart). When destination is not defined, then User should be redirected to Homepage.
  • Title text will be changed dynamically. Title format is "XX ITEM(S) $YYYY", where XX is a product counter and YYYY is Grand Total for the order.
  •  Functional tabs: Cart and Checkout
  • Tabs are shown below TopBar
  • ‘Checkout’ tab will be opened. This tab will be highlighted with line and another font color.
  •  ‘Cart’ tab is available/clickable. After clicking the "Cart" tab  - Shopping cart popup/page will be shown.
  • Sections/fields
  • GENERAL behavior
  • Sections, which are available for editing will be highlighted with blue frame, blue title, or with blue  icons (were no title (email and delivery method). Exception: Promo code/gift card (it's always editable)
  • Sections with entered data  will have black title/icons
  • Sections with errors - red frame, red titles, red icons
  • Whole section is clickable
  • Email section 
  • input field
  • View mode elements: Icon, Placeholder [Enter Email address], ’Add button’ and arrow[mobile]
  • upon clicking the whole field (anywhere) the Contact information pop-up [mobile], section [desktop] is opened. See details in  CONTACT INFORMATION/ LOGIN TO YOUR ACCOUNT 
  • Entered mode elements: Icon,Entered data, arrow [mobile]
  • [customer]: the field will be auto-populated with the customer email and won’t be editable
  • the field is always visible
  • Delivery section
  • always visible
  • Disabled till the ‘Email’ field is entered/auto-populated

  •  If there are any validation issues - it should be correctly mirrored on the popup/page. The order will not be placed.
  • Place order button is  be sticky on the mobile
  • CMS-block- content will be manageable. The content see in CONTENT CHECK-LIST
