  • Title; [Contact Information]
  •  'Email address' input  field
  • A user is able to enter the email address.
  • there is validation on email format upon the user enters the data and moves the cursor out
  • empty by default,
  • placeholder [Email Address] is displayed
  • auto-populated if the email address was saved before 
  • Text label
  • [We will send your order confirmation here]
  • 'Login' link
  • A user is redirected to Login Page.
  • 'Continue' button
  • Upon clicking the button:
  • If the validation fails, the current page is opened, the error message should be shown below the input field
  • If the field is empty,  the system shows error messages of mandatory field.
  •  If the validation passes, the system checks if the entered email already exists:
  • if no , the entered email should be saved, the user is redirected to Checkout Page
  • if yes, the user is redirected to [Login to your account]  pop-up (see description below) ([Login To Your Account] pop-up)
  • The input fields on the pop-up will be mandatory or optional in accordance with CMS settings
  •  [Login To Your Account] pop-up elements ([Desktop] has the same elements, instead of Back icon, displayed via section):
  • TopBar: [mobile] Back button, Title
  • [mobile] When a user clicks the Back button they are redirected to the [Contact Information] Pop-up.
  • Title: [Login To Your Account]
  • User's email
  • email which was entered on the [Contact Information] Pop-up.
  • the ‘letter’ icon before email
  • [Not your email? Go back] link below the email
  • When a user clicks the link they are redirected to the [Contact Information] Pop-up (see above).
  •  Text label with welcome message
  • [Welcome back!]
  • [Enter your password to continue]
  • Password Input field
  • A user is able to enter the password.
  • There will be icon to ‘see’ entered password
  • When a user clicks the icon the password becomes readable for a user.
  •  'Login' button
  • below the password input field
  • Upon clicking the button all field data will be validated. Default Magento validation applies
  • A user is redirected to the Checkout page after successful validation.
  • In case of password validation is failed then an error message will be shown on the page.  The message "Sorry, the password you have entered is incorrect" will be shown
  • Forgot password  link
  • below the Login button
  • label:  [Forgot password?]
  • When a user clicks the link they are redirected to the Forgot password page.
  • separator with label [or]
  • 'Continue as guest' button
  • When a user clicks the button they are redirected to the Checkout page as a Guest
  • The entered Email will be saved and reflected on the Checkout page
  • The input fields on the pop-up will be mandatory or optional in accordance with CMS settings

  1. ADDING/EDITING DELIVERY ADDRESS

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • Guest User and the customer (if there is no Addresses in the Address book) are able to add/edit the delivery address via [Delivery Address] pop-up.
  • "Delivery Address" popup will be shown after User clicks on "Delivery " section on Checkout age
  • Delivery Address pop-up elements ([Desktop] has the same elements, instead of Back icon,  via section:
  • TopBar
  • TopBar is shown on the top of the page. It has 2 elements: [mobile] Back-button and Title
  • Title text is ¨Delivery Address¨.
  • [mobile] When User clicks the ‘Back’ button - pop-up will be closed and User will get back to Checkout. If there is entered data, which is not validated and confirmed yet - it won’t be saved.
  • Contact Details block elements:
  • Title "Contact Details"
  • The following input fields: First Name, Last Name,  Phone Number
  • all fields have the corresponding placeholders
  • Delivery Address block elements:
  • "Delivery Address" title
  •  Next fields: Company (Optional)- input field, Street Address Line 1-  input field, Street Address  Line 2 (Optional)-  input field, Country - drop-down,  City -  input field, State -  input field or drop-down, Postcode - input field
  • all input fields have the corresponding placeholders
  • drop-downs have the corresponding title and the placeholder “Select option..”
  • "State" field can be shown as input field or as a dropdown:
  • as an input field, if the country field isn't entered  OR there are no predefined "State" options for the selected country.
  • as a drop-down, if there are predefined options for a particular (selected) country. Options will be updated based on the selected option into "Country" dropdown
  • "Use This Address" button
  • Upon clicking the button all field data will be validated. BE validation applies
  • If there are no validation issues for the field/dropdowns - changes will  be saved. The Checkout page will be opened.
  • If there are any validation issues for the field/dropdowns - changes will not be saved and related fields will get "error" state. If there are any related validation tips - they will be shown.
  • See the specification for address attributes  in File/link to customer profile attributes is here.
  •  When there are no previously saved data for the fields/dropdowns - they will be shown in "default" (empty) state..
  •  Vertical scroll bar should be available in case a lot of fields are expected on popup.

  • Radio button (mandatory)
  • Method Name (mandatory)
  • Title (if set)
  • Price (mandatory)
  • Error message (if set)
  • Delivery methods will  be listed according to their priority (if priority is set by admin)
  • The following delivery method will be available and manageable:
  • Flat rate
  • Free shipping
  • Table Rates [BAT-017-CR], .csv file for import and configuration details are to be provided by BAT team
  • User is able to select only one delivery method from the list
  • When User tries to choose not-applicable delivery method, then special error message will be shown:
  • If the error message is set by admin  for delivery method - then this particular message will be used.
  • if the error message is not set by admin for delivery method - then the message  text: "This delivery method is not available. To use this delivery method, please contact us." will be shown
  • If there are no available delivery methods in the list, then a special message will be shown: "Sorry, no methods are available for this order at this time. Make sure you fill in the delivery address."

  • Vertical scroll bar should be available on the popup in case there are a lot of delivery methods.

  1. [BAT-II-0089] SIMPLIFICATION OF ADDRESS SELECTION AND VERIFICATION

FEATURE HIGHLIGHTS:

AREAS

SUMMARY

Is this a new Feature or a Change of existing Feature?

Change

What is the Business Need behind this Feature implementation?

Reduce the likelihood of entering a non-existent address

Is this feature applied to all resolutions?

Yes

Does this Feature require change in the admin panel?

Yes

Are there any dependencies with other Features?

Adding/editing address

Are there any dependencies with Integrations or 3rd party systems?

No

Applicable for both logged in and guest users?

Yes

Is this Feature market specific?

Indonesia

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0089-US1

As a system, I want to consistently receive address data from the client in order to avoid using invalid addresses.

BAT-II-0089-US2

As an administrator, I want the user to fill in the address in stages, selecting the necessary address data from the suggested values

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. New address attribute "District" (Bahasa: kecamatan/Kelurahan) is added
  2. Two entities "City" and "District" will be created in the back office.
  1. The admin is able to add/edit/remove items from these entities.
  2. When manually creating, for each item, the admin must specify a parent entity.
    For example, when creating a new district, its city will need to be determined 
  1. The website admin is able to upload an external file with provinces, cities and districts
  1. Each district must have a city and province filled
  2. If any of these values (province, city) are missing in the load file, this line will be skipped when loading
  1. the corresponding error will be written to the log.
  1. When a user selects the country "Indonesia" on the front-end side , the following fields presented as dropdowns:
  1. Province
  2. City
  3. District
  1. Data for dropdowns is taken from the back office
  1. The fields are dependent on each other. So each province has its own set of available cities. Each city has its own set of available districts
  1. If the user has already selected a province, then only the cities of this province will be shown in the city dropdown. Likewise for the district field.
  2. If the user tries to specify a city but the province value is empty, the drop-down menu will display "Please select a province first" instead of the available options. Likewise for the district field.
  1. Validation of the entered values will be added for the Street address line 1:
  1. At least 10 characters. If no an error message is displayed:
  1. “At least 10 characters in the address” (PK)
  2. “Setidaknya 10 karakter di alamat”  (IND)
  1. At least 1 digit.  If no an error message is displayed:
  1. “The house number is not specified” (PK)
  2. “Nomor rumah tidak ditentukan” (IND)
  1. This approach will be used on all address editing forms on the site (My account, Checkout -Shipping address, Billing address)
  2. All other validations, dropdown field behavior  and the way how the shipping cost is calculated will be based on the current solution (post code will still be the main source to identify the shipping cost)

  1. APPLY PROMO CODE/GIFT CARD

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • Promo Code / Gift Card" pop-up [mobile]/ expanded accordion [desktop] will be shown after User clicks on "Promo Code / Gift Card" section on Checkout page
  • Popup elements (Desktop will have the same elements instead of Back icon):
  • TopBar It has 2 elements: Back-button [mobile] and Title.
  • Title text will be "Promo Code / Gift Card"
  • [mobile] When User clicks on the Back button - popup will  be closed and User will get back to Checkout
  • if there is entered data, which is not validated and confirmed yet - it should not be processed. If promo code/gift card was entered and successfully verified - discount will  be provided and Grand Total (= Total on UI)  order price will  be recalculated/updated.
  • The applied promo code/gift card  will be displayed in the special Section for applied Promo Code/Gift Card
  • [desktop] if the user clicks ‘-’, the accordion will be collapsed
  • Functional tabs
  • "Promo Code"
  • "Gift Card" available/clickable
  • After User clicks on "Gift Card" tab  - Gift Card popup
  • The  active (opened tab) will  be highlighted with the line in the bottom and different font color
  • Promo Code tab is active by default
  • Promo Code block is displayed if “Promo Code"  tab is active/opened
  • Elements:Title , Promo Code field
  • Title is "Enter a Promo Code"
  • Promo Code field: Default state placeholder and label for the field is "Promo Code".
  • "Apply" button
  • The button will be always available/active
  • Upon clicking the Apply  button - field data should be validated
  • Validation error message: "The Promo Code is not valid. Please, verify the code and try again."
  • If there are no any validation issues for the field:
  •  promo code should be processed successfully and discount should be provided.
  • [Applied Promo code] section should be displayed with the applied Promo code.
  • Promo code field should be displayed in the  default state
  • If there are any validation issues for the field:
  • discount should not  be provided
  • Promo Code field should get an "error" state, related error message will be shown. "The Promo Code is not valid. Please, verify the code and try again." or "This is a required field"
  • [Applied Promo Code] section will be displayed above the input field for promo code.
  • Each applied Promo code will  have the title [Promo code], Promo code name and Remove link.
  • Upon click  Remove link
  • promo code will be removed from the order
  • related discount will be annulled
  • the section [Applied promo code] will  be updated or disappear if the last promo code was removed.
  • Gift Cart block is is displayed if “Promo Code"  tab is active/opened
  • Elements: Title, Gift Card input field, Check Balance block, Redeem button
  • Title is "Enter Gift Card Number"
  • Gift Card input field: The default state placeholder: "Gift Card Number".
  • Check Balance block will  be placed below the Gift Card input field.
  • Check Balance block elements: "Check Balance" link and "Current Balance" information
  • "Check Balance" link is always available/active
  • Upon click on the link  - Gift Card field data will  be validated.
  • If there are no validation issues for the entered Gift Card code, then  "Current Balance" information will be shown. The Gift Card field will get "verified" state.
  •  ‘Current Balance’ information will be shown if the user clicks Check Balance link. It contains the message: "Your current gift card balance is [actual balance] Expires: [date]"
  • If the expiration date is not provided the text label "Expires: [date]"  is not displayed. The block with gift card balance remains till the page reloads (the user makes some action)
  • If there are any validation issues for the field: the corresponding error message will  be shown.
  • When a user does not enter the gift card code and clicks the button to check balance, the corresponding error message for the mandatory field will  be shown.
  • ‘Redeem" button will be shown below the Gift Card block and Check Balance block.
  • The button is  always available/active
  • Upon click on the button - field data will  be validated.
  •  If there are no validation issues for the entered gift card code:
  • Gift Card will  be processed successfully and Grand Total (= Total on UI) will  be correctly recalculated for the order
  • Gift Card field will  get "default" state
  • Applied gift card will be displayed in the Applied Gift Card block
  • If there are any validation issues for the field:
  • Gift Card will not be processed
  • Gift Card field will get "error" state, related error message will be shown.
  • if Gift Card with "0" balance is applied, an error message ‘The gift card code couldn't be added. Verify your information and try again’ will be displayed.
  • Applied Gift Card block will be placed above Gift Card block after the gift card was successfully redeemed.
  • Title: "Applied Gift Card"
  • Each applied Gift Card will have a Gift Card Number displayed in the title, the redeemed balance below the title and Remove link.  
  • Upon click  Remove link
  • gift card  will be removed from the order
  • related discount will be annulled
  • the section [Applied Gift Card] will  be updated or disappear if the gift card  was removed.

VISUAL EXAMPLES:

There is no VE.

Assumption: No mockups to be provided, development team to work directly from brand guidelines with an agreed set of changes to be described and defined without any visual source of requirements.

  1. [BAT-004-CR] SOCIAL SELLER AFFILIATE ATTRIBUTION

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • Users will have an ability to enter a Referral code during check-out.
  • a text field, optional, no validation required
  • Storefront label: Kode Referensi, Attribute code: social_seller_referral
  • both logged in and guest users will have this text field
  • users will be able to add/update/delete data in this text field before order is submitted
  • Admin don’t need this input field for orders placed via the admin panel.
  • Admin don’t need an ability to add/update/delete data in this text field after Order is submitted.
  • System will save the value of the “social_seller_referral” on order entity level, after order was successfully submitted from storefront.

ASSUMPTIONS AND CONSTRAINTS:

  • Codes will be generated and distributed outside of the Magento admin panel and storefront.
  • No integrations with loyalty and commission systems.
  • No integration with social seller apps.
  • No integration to aCommerce in order data.
  • No custom reporting interface on the Magento admin panel.
  • No loyalty points attribution for orders with Referral code.

  1. [BAT-003-CR] AGE VERIFICATION BASED ON KPT ID

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • Users will see a message below the header that will inform about legal age during checkout flow.
  • Message will be implemented via a CMS block
  • Admin will have an ability to manage text inside the message using Page Builder functionality.
  • Users will have to enter a KTP ID before order could be submitted.
  • upon click on ‘Place Order’ button described in the following section CHECKOUT PAGE user will see a pop-up:
  • Validate ID title
  • KTP ID placeholder in text input field
  • Validate button
  • upon click validation of the data submitted in the KTP ID text input field will be performed
  • validation logic will be hardcoded and not manageable
  • if validation is passed -> ORDER SUCCESS page will be displayed
  • if validation is failed -> validation error message will be displayed, user will remain on the validation pop-up
  • Error message text: You must be 18 or above years old to place an order.
  • Error message text won’t be manageable in admin panel
  • Cancel button
  • upon click user will close pop-up, no order placement will happen, user will see CHECKOUT PAGE  with all previously filled in data

VALIDATION LOGIC:

Date of Birth retrieval from KTP ID:

  • Tanggal Lahir = Day of Birth, DD format
  • if female, the tanggal lahir will add 40, if male using actual tanggal lahir
  • Bulan Lahir = Month of Birth, MM format
  • Tahun Lahir = Year of Birth, YY format

  • Example above,  a female's DOB is 04/03/91, (44-40 = 04)

Example: Male KTP

  • KTP ID: 3173071105820005
  • Character 7-12 is the date of birth in ddmmyy format (110582)
  • Is dd greater than 31? No so I am male.
  • The male date of birth is 11 May 1982

Example: Female KTP

  • KTP ID: 3173075105820005
  • Character 7-12 is is the date of birth in ddmmyy format (510582)
  • Is dd greater than 31? Yes so I am female
  • For a female, the dd is 51-40 = 11
  • The female date of birth is 11 May 1982

After DOB data is retrieved, the following validation is to be performed:

  • current date (dd/mm/yy) - DOB (dd/mm/yy) =
  • 18 years or above -> validation passed, user is valid to place an order
  • 17 years or below -> validation failed, user is not valid to place an order

ASSUMPTIONS AND CONSTRAINTS:

  • Data submitted within the input field won’t be stored in the database.User will need to enter this data again upon next purchase.
  • Both logged in and guest users will need to validate the KTP ID upon Order Placement
  • No limitation of validation retries will be implemented, user will be able to try as many times as he/she wants
  • Blank input field will be equal to invalid age

  1. ORDER SUCCESS

BLOCK BEHAVIOR:

  • Order Success page will be shown after the user  places an order successfully.
  • Page sections:
  • "Thank You" section elements:
  • Related order number
  • Related email
  • "Continue Shopping" button
  • After clicking the  "Continue Shopping" button User will  be redirected to the Homepage.
  • [guest user] "Create an Account" section elements:
  • Title: "Create an account for future use"
  • Text block: "You can track your order status by creating an account
  • Email Address  field. It will  be pre-filled with related email addresses (used during order creation). The field will be disabled, it will not be possible to edit the data.
  • Input fields:  First Nam ,Last Name fiel, Password
  • all input fields have the corresponding placeholders
  • First Name and Last Name will  be pre-set with related data (used during order creation procedure). (from the delivery address, if the delivery address isn't available - from billing address).
  • all fields are editable
  • "Create an Account" button
  • After click on "Create an Account" button - all field data should be validated. Default Magento validation applies
  • If there are no any validation issues, then a new customer account will  be created, User will  be redirected to Homepage.
  • If validation is failed, then related input field(s) will be shown in error-state and error message(s) will  be shown below the field(s).
  • The user registered via Order Confirmation page will see the order (which ID was displayed on the Order Confirmation page)  in My Orders section in My Account.

  • BNI
  • BANK BRI
  • CIMB BANK
  • Mandiri
  • PermataBank
  • BRI
  • E-Pay BRI
  • LinkAja
  • PermataNet
  • OCBC Bank
  • ATM Bersama, Prima, ALTO
  • ATM BCA
  1. Payment categorization will be defined in the mapping list: productCode - category
  • If the category contains at least one active payment option, then this category will be displayed on the list of categories
  • if there is no active payment options for the category, the category will be hidden from the list of categories
  1. All categories will be collapsed by default and user will need to click on a category to open it to select a payment option that belongs to the category
  • upon click on the category, a list of payment options will be displayed
  • all payments will be displayed in a line by line with radio buttons
  • each payment will have an icon and the text name of the payment option that is retrieved from EsPay
  • when a payment option is selected, the user proceeds to the checkout with this selected option
  1. User should click on the ‘>’ next to the selected payment option to be able to go back to the previous step and change the payment option there.
  2. User can expand all categories with drop-down options without closing the previously opened category on the desktop version.
  3. Only one payment option can be selected at a time.
  4. No payment option inside a category will be pre-selected by default.
  5. Sort order of the payment methods won’t be manageable in admin panel and the sequence how payments are displayed inside the category will be based on how the payment methods will be retrieved from EsPay
  6. No changes to the current flow of the payment process will be introduced
  7. No CoD payment method changes will be introduced

  • "Weight (and above)" weight_from

  2. No Regular delivery shipping method changes will be introduced.
  3. When creating a new method, it must be added to the shipping methods mapping table of the Acommerce integration settings

BAT-II-0107-US1

BAT-II-0107-US3

As a user, I want to be able to select new shipping methods on the Checkout page

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. New shipping method will be configured based on the “Extended shipping rates” module
  1. The basis for determining the cost (rate) of delivery will be the number of items in the cart and the destination City
  2. A new rule for applying shipping method rates will be developed: the destination city is in the list (city/email mapping table)
  • Will be displayed as the "Within city" checkbox for each method rate
  • When the checkbox is active, the shipping method rate will be shown only for those cities that are in the city/email mapping table
  • Those rates for which the checkbox is inactive will be displayed for all other manually filled cities
  1. A site admin will be able to manage method rates (quantity of items and their shipping cost) via BO
  2. A site admin will be able to manage the method title via BO
  3. Shipping method currency - Rs
  4. If the shipping rate cannot be applied (cart state does not match the application), it should not appear in the list of available methods

ASSUMPTIONS AND CONSTRAINTS:

  1. The proposed option does not allow the use of specific discounts for specific cities from the list. That is, the specified shipping cost will be applied to all cities in the list

Cart price rules

Are there any dependencies with Integrations or 3rd party systems?

No

Applicable for both logged in and guest users?

Yes

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0093

As a user, I want to see the coupons available to me on the site in order to be able to apply them

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. The site admin is able to enable/disable the Coupon Wallet functionality in BO
  2. The site admin is able to show/hide a cart price rule (with coupon) in the Wallet
  1. By default, this option “Show” will be selected for all new cart pricing rules.
  1. Coupon wallet will be displayed on the checkout page
  1. Displayed above the "Enter promo code" field in the form of an accordion
  2. Collapsed by default
  3. Displays no more than two coupons tile at the same time when opened
  • If there are more than two coupons, a scroll bar appears
  1. Each coupon tile contains:
  • Promo code
  • For rules that use auto-generated codes, the code will not be displayed
  • Cart price rule name
  • Cart price rule description (one line)
  • If the description does not fit on one line, the ‘More’ link appears at the end of the line.
    Only after clicking it, the description expands in its entirety.
  • Valid date
  • ‘Apply’ button
  • When clicked, the coupon is automatically inserted into the "Promo code" field and is applied
  1. The user can check the available coupons via MyAccount
  1. New menu item "Coupons" (Kupon) will be added
  2. A new page with a list of coupons will be added to MyAccount
  • By clicking the apply button, the selected promo code will be saved and automatically applied on the checkout page if during the same session the user goes to the checkout.
  1. If the coupon has expired, it will still be displayed in the wallet, but without the option to select it.
  1. The website admin will be able to remove it from the wallet by disabling the settings in the card price role in the back office.
  2. 7 days after the expiration date of the coupon, it should automatically change to "do not display in the wallet"

  • Error message text won’t be manageable in admin panel
  • Cancel button
  • upon click user will close pop-up, no order placement will happen, user will see CHECKOUT PAGE  with all previously filled in data

VALIDATION LOGIC is consistent as deceived in here

As a user, I want to see a list of blog post tiles on the Blog Index page, so that I can click on any of them and go to Blog Post View page of the corresponding post

Each blog post tile will have Featured Image, Date, Title, Short Description (can be cut if too long) and Read More text link

BAT-II-0278-US11

As an admin, I want to specify OG Metadata per each blog post

BAT-II-0278-US12

BAT-II-0278-US13

MODULES:

A third party module will be used to meet the current need:
https://batdigital.visualstudio.com/Magento/_wiki/wikis/Magento.wiki/22644/Enable-Blog-extenstion 

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  • module configuration is only supported to the scope identified as MVP, changing the settings to other configurations will not be supported/reflected on the storefront without additional development
  • user will be able to navigate to the Blog Index page from header menu or from footer (links are to be added by each market’s content management agency)
  • posts will be created and managed in the admin panel according to the supported functionality

NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  • SEO
  • Meta Data configuration for Blog is to be supported for Blog Index and Blog Post View pages
  • OG tags configuration is to be supported for Blog Post View pages
  • Featured Image Alt tag configuration is to be supported
  • URLs
  • Blog Index page and Blog Post View page URL key configuration is to be supported

PERMISSIONS REQUIREMENTS:

  • admin users that have access to the specific website should only be able to change configuration of the blog module and see/manage/create posts for their specific scope level
  • super admins are able to update configurations of the module and post content per any market, including default scope level

BLOG INDEX PAGE ELEMENTS:

  1. Blog Title
  1. manageable in the admin panel (Stores -> Configuration -> Magefan Extensions -> Blog -> Blog Index Page -> Title)
  2. Text will always be displayed in UPPERCASE on the storefront

  1. Blog Post Listing block
  1. Blog Post sorting on this page will be managed in the admin panel according to the configuration (Stores -> Configuration -> Magefan Extensions -> Blog -> Blog Index Page -> Posts Sort By)
  2. Maximum 12 posts will be displayed per page, not manageable
  3. Only posts that are set as recent will be displayed on this page (on Post creation page ‘Include in Recent Posts’ is set to Yes)

  1. Page Switcher block
  1. will be displayed if the amount of posts is exceeding the maximum amount of posts that can be displayed per page
  2. user will be able to switch between blog listing pages using this element
  1. currently selected page will be highlighted as per design
  2. left and right arrows will only be displayed if there is a page to navigate after or before the currently selected page (i.e. if 1st page is selected, there will be no left arrow)
  3. click on the right or left arrow will switch page to a next or a previous page correspondingly

  1. Blog Post Listing Tile
  1. Featured Image
  1. managed on the Post Details in admin panel
  1. Publish Date
  1. managed on the Post Details in admin panel
  2. date format [DD Month YYYY]
  3. only english language for month will be supported for now
  1. Post Title
  1. managed on the Post Details in admin panel
  2. Text will always be displayed in UPPERCASE on the storefront
  3. Length of the title is not limited in the admin panel, but should not exceed 2 lines to look as per design
  1. Short Content
  1. managed on the Post Details in admin panel
  2. if too long, will be cut with ellipsis (...)
  1. READ MORE text link, not manageable, target URL -> blog post view page
  1. position is fixed and does not depend on the above content
  1. upon click on anywhere on the tile user will be redirected to the blog post view page

BLOG POST VIEW PAGE ELEMENTS:

  1. Featured Image
  1. same as on Blog Index page

  1. Post Title
  1. same as on Blog Index page
  1. Publish Date
  1. same as on Blog Index page
  1. Social Sharing icons TOP BLOCK
  1. DEPRECATED, not MVP

  1. Post Content
  1. managed on the Post Details in the admin panel
  2. Page Builder elements that are supported by Luft will be available to use

  1. Social Sharing icons BOTTOM BLOCK
  1. DEPRECATED, not MVP

  1. Related Posts block
  1. only displayed when Stores -> Configuration -> MAGEFAN EXTENSION -> Blog -> Post Page (Post View) -> Display Related Posts is set to Yes
  2. Related posts block title
  1. not manageable, styled per brand as on design
  1. VIEW ALL text link
  1. not manageable, upon click on it user will be redirected to the Blog Index Page
  1. Related posts
  1. assigned by admin manually on Post Details page
  2. not more than 3 blog posts will be displayed
  3. display order will be based on the sort order in the related posts assignment (position by drag and drop)
  4. tiles are same as per Blog Post Listing Tile
  5. if no posts assigned as related, we will still show block title and view all text link

  1. [BAT-II-0016] PUSH NOTIFICATIONS TO CONSUMERS IN PWA (APPROVED)

FEATURE HIGHLIGHTS:

AREAS

SUMMARY

Is this a new Feature or a Change of existing Feature?

Change

What is the Business Need behind this Feature implementation?

Provide a better user experience for a user regarding to the notification

Is this feature applied to all resolutions?

Yes

Does this Feature require change in the admin panel?

Yes

No

Applicable for both logged in and guest users?

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0016-US1

As an admin, I want to manage the notifications via admin panel

BAT-II-0016-US2

As a guest and logged-in user, I want to subscribe/unsubscribe the push notifications from the website

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Admin is able to manage (add, edit, delete) notifications via the admin panel in order to configure the notifications in accordance with the business needs. Following default attributes will be included for each notification:
  1. Active: toggle field
    It is set as Yes by default. Switch to No will inactive the notification.
  2. Title: input field (is mandatory)
    It is the title of the notification message
  3. Description: input field (is mandatory)
    It is the description of the notification message
  4. Destination URL: input field
    Destination URL to be displayed in the notification message. Upon clicking the URL of the message, the user will be redirected to the corresponding page.
  5. Icon: image field
    Icon to be displayed in the notification message
  6. Image: image field
    Image to be displayed in the notification message
  7. Send Time: date field (is mandatory)
    Set send time of the notification
  8. Store View: multiple selection field  (is mandatory)
    Set which store view you would like to send the notification
  1. Admin is able to see the list of notification subscribers, delete the selected subscribers.
  2. Admin is able to send notification to all the subscribers, or send specified notifications to the selected subscribers manually.
  3. A  guest and a logged-in user is able to subscribe/unsubscribe the push notifications from the website storefront.
  1. User is able to redirect to Notifications ‘Settings’ page by clicking the ‘SETTINGS’ item under the 'Main Menu'
  2. The ‘SETTINGS’ page contains the following elements:
  1. ‘Back’ button. Upon clicking on the button, user will be redirected back to the previous page where the user click into the ‘SETTINGS’ page
  2. Title ‘SETTINGS’
  3. ‘Notification’ tab under ‘SETTINGS’ title
  1. Upon clicking the ‘Notification’ tab on the ‘SETTINGS’ page, the user is able to redirect to the ‘Notification’ page. The Notification page contains the following elements:
  1. ‘Back’ button. Upon clicking on the button, a user will be redirected back to the ‘SETTINGS’  page.
  2. Title ‘Notifications’
  3. Section for managing general notification settings with toggle ‘Allow Notifications’:
  • Possible states for the toggle "ON" and "Off" , always enabled
  • ‘Allow Notifications’ toggle is "OFF" (turned to the left)  by default.
  1. The user who subscribed for the “Allow Notifications” will receive allowed notifications with the system's default styling.

SUPPORTED BROWSERS:

For desktop, popular browsers that have Push Notifications feature are supported.

For mobile devices, iOS devices are not supported due to OS security limitations; Android devices work and the notification message looks like native push notifications.

The following latest version of the major browsers will be tested as a part of the implementation:

  1. REFERRAL MIGRATION TO MAGENTO

The initial migration is planned to be done by eWave MSS team on Request from BAT team.

The migration will include the following:

Mass update in the DB assignment to a Tier for Social Sellers

  • BAT team will provide the emails of the Social Sellers who has registered on the platform
  • MSS team will update the Tier assignment to Social Seller Tier for the emails provided in the list from BAT team

The migration will NOT include creation of the relations between existing accounts ‘Advocate <-> Referral’. This migration can be done by users themselves. They will use the referral link of the Advocate and go to the website:

  • guest users will need to register/log in the account so that the system will create the relation ‘Advocate <-> Referral’.
  • user can be assigned as a referral to only ONE Advocate, so if the user has already registered/logged in with another referral link, system will not update the relation to a new Advocate

  • Include discount for Earning rules - No
  • Include tax for Earning rules - No
  • Include tax for Spending rules - No
  • Apply Spending Points Discount After Tax - Use Magento settings
  • Allow to earn points from shipping charges - No
  • Allow to spend points for shipping charges - Yes
  • Allow to place orders with grand total = 0 - No
  • Allow to display product points as currency equivalent - No
  • Allow to display maximum number of possible points for configurable products - No

  • Include Tax - No

  1. REFERRAL URL STRUCTURE

The referral URL will be formed based on the following logic:

[website][page][unique_referral_code]

Example:

https://www.velo.com/id/id/register/VYRcECZW/

When a user accesses the website using the referral link and registers and account / logs in to an account without affiliation, this user will become a referral to a user that provided that link (whose unique referral code is used).

  1. REFERRAL TIER ASSIGNMENT

Tier assignment will be done automatically only for the General Users, assignment to all other Tiers will be done manually by the admin on the Customer level.

For General User Tier rule will be created as follows:

Where the min amount of points/currency will be set as 0, meaning that all users will automatically fall under this tier unless it is not specified in the other way.

For assignment to any other Tier, the admin will go to Customers -> Customer Details page -> Account Information tab -> Reward Tier dropdown and set the required tier for the customer selecting the value from the drop-down.

  1. REFERRAL TIER MASS UPDATE

There will be no mass update of the tier for the MVP as confirmed by the vendor of the module.

Can be added at a later phase as a customization. Should be added to the backlog and prioritized.

MOBILE

DESKTOP

  1. REWARD POINTS REDEMPTION (CHECKOUT PAGE)

  1. Reward Points block will be in accordion format. It is displayed above the “Enter Promo Code" block and collapsed by default. The expanded accordion will be shown after the user clicks on it.

Elements: Title, Short Description, Reward Points iInput Field, Use Maximum checkbox,  Apply button and [Applied Reward Points] section after Reward Points were applied.

  • Title:  
  • Use Reward Points (PK)
  • Gunakan Poin Imbalan (IND)
  • Short Description:
  • You have X Reward Points (PK)
  • Anda memiliki X Poin Imbalan (IND)
  • (X is the Reward Points that available in user’s account)
  • Reward Points input field with default state placeholder
  • Enter the amount of points to spend. (PK)
  • Masukkan jumlah poin yang akan dibelanjakan. (IND)
  • A checkbox with text
  • Use Maximum X Reward Points (PK)
  • Gunakan Poin Hadiah X Maksimum (IND)
  • (X is the maximum number of points that can be used)
  • Upon ticking the checkbox:
  • The maximum number of points that can be used will be added/updated to the Reward Point input field and applied
  • [Applied Reward Points] section will be displayed with the applied Reward Points
  • The corresponding Reward Points spent and Reward Discount will be shown in the summary block of Checkout page
  • Apply button:
  • The button is always available / active
  • Upon click on the button - field data should be validated
  • When a user does not enter any Reward Points and clicks the Apply button, the error message “This is a required field.” will be shown.
  • If there are no validation issues for the field:
  • The Reward Points will be processed successfully
  • [Applied Reward Points] section will be displayed with the applied Reward Points
  • The corresponding Reward Points spent and Reward Discount will be shown in the summary block of Checkout page
  • If there are any validation issues for the field:
  • If the data input is a non-digital number or the number input is larger than the maximum use amount
  • “Use Maximum” checkbox will be ticked
  • The maximum number of points that can be used will be updated to the Reward Points input field and applied
  • [Applied Reward Points] section will be displayed with the applied Reward Points
  • The corresponding Reward Points spent and Reward Discount will be shown in the summary block of Checkout page
  • if the data input is less than the minimum use amount
  • The minimum number of points that can be used will be updated to the Reward Points input field and applied
  • [Applied Reward Points] section will be displayed with the applied Reward Points
  • The corresponding Reward Points spent and Reward Discount will be shown in the summary block of Checkout page
  • [Applied Reward Points] section will be displayed below the Reward Points block title once after Reward Points were applied successfully.
    The Applied Reward Points will have following elements:
  • X Reward Points were applied (X is the actual Reward Points that user applied to the order)
  • Cancel Points button:
    Upon click on the button
  • The applied Reward Points will be removed from the order
  • The corresponding Reward Points spent and Reward Discount will be removed from the summary block of Checkout page
  • The [Applied Reward Points] section will disappear. The Reward point input field and Apply button will be displayed again.

  1. Summary block:

If user applied the Reward Points successfully

  • “You Spend: X Reward Points” line will be displayed below “Subtotal” line
  • “Rewards Discount: X” line will be displayed above “Order Total” line

If user cancelled the Reward Points redemption successfully

  • The “You Spend”, “Reward Discount” lines and the related discount will be removed

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0128-US1

As a site admin, I want be able to assign a coupon to specific user

BAT-II-0128-US2

As a site admin, I want be able to remove a coupon from a user

BAT-II-0128-US3

As a logged in user, I want no one else to be able to use my personal coupon

BAT-II-0128-US4

As a logged in user, I want my personal coupon to appear in my Coupon Wallet

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. When creating/managing  a coupon cart price rule a site admin is able to assign (and remove) a specific customer to a coupon
  1. setting is available only for coupons with auto generation
  2. setting is available in the "Manage Coupon Codes" accordion
  3. A coupon is assigned to a specific user by specifying their email address on the coupon line in the table
  1. When filling out the email in the coupon table, a search in the customer database is triggered and the first five emails corresponding to the typed characters are pulled
  1. A site admin can’t assign a coupon to email that is not in the site database
  2. By clicking on the proposed email, it is inserted into the email field
  1. A site admin is able to reassign a coupon to other customer manually
  2. Only a customer with the specified email address can see such a personal promo code in their coupon wallet
  3. Only a customer with the specified email address can use such a personal promo code
  4. Noone can see in the Wallet or use coupons, which haven't assigned to a specific user

CONFIGURATION REQUIREMENTS:

  1. BO > Marketing > Cart Price rules > [a rule] > Enable personal coupon setting should be created
  1. Yes/no
  1. BO > Marketing > Cart Price rules > [a rule]:
  1. Coupon: Specific coupon
  2. Ticked ‘Use Auto Generation’
  3. Enable personal coupons: yes
  4. Uses per Coupon: 1
  5. Customers per Coupon: 1  (always 1, the setting should be hidden)

  • Toggle button

  1. a coupon from the selected card price rule is assigned to the user:
  • Validity in days is set up to [‘Coupon validity’ value]
  • Email: [email of the user who met the Earning rule conditions]
  1. A successful message appears on the screen stating that the new coupon was successfully received
  • Text: “Congratulations! You have received a new coupon”

    It has already been added to your     coupon wallet

  1. If there is no available coupons in the cart price rule,  a notification message is displayed

  • Text: TBC

  • the Coupon assignment process will be performed in [Delay in issuing coupon] days
  • a notification message should be displayed
  • Text: TBC
  1. If ‘Delay…’ is disabled fo the rule
  • the Coupon assignment process is performed
  1. [FE] A  user who registered using a referral link should be able to immediately receive a coupon with a limited period of use
  2. [FE] A logged in user whose referral made the first purchase should be able to receive a limited-time coupon after [X] days.
  1. where [X] - amount of days set up in ‘Delay in assigning a coupon for, days’ setting in BO

  • numeric input field
  • store level setting

  • personal coupons CONFIGURATION REQUIREMENTS:

FEATURE HIGHLIGHTS:

AREAS

SUMMARY

Is this a new Feature or a Change of existing Feature?

Change

What is the Business Need behind this Feature implementation?

Legal Requirements that only people 18 or above years old can have an account and place an order on website

Is this feature applied to all resolutions?

Yes

Does this Feature require change in the admin panel?

Yes

Are there any dependencies with other Features?

No

Are there any dependencies with Integrations or 3rd party systems?

No

Applicable for both logged in and guest users?

No

No

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0029-US1

As a user, I want to input a National ID during registration before I can create an account.

BAT-II-0029-US2

As a guest user, I want to input a National ID during checkout before I can place an order

BAT-II-0029-US3

As a registered & logged in user, I will not see National ID block during checkout

BAT-II-0029-US4

As a user, I want to see National ID in Account Information page

BAT-II-0029-US5

As an Indonesia user, I want to see Age Verified in Account Information page

BAT-II-0029-US6

As an admin, I want to disable edit of National ID and Age Verified in Account Information

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. On Registration page described in the following section REGISTRATION PAGE 
  1. User will see a new attribute (mandatory text input field) ‘National ID’ above ‘Date of Birth’ field
  2. User will have to input their National ID before they can create an account
  • Upon click ‘CREATE ACCOUNT’ button on Registration Page after user input their National ID, validation of the data submitted in the National ID field will be performed:
  • Validation logic will be hardcoded and not manageable
  • If validation is passed -> user will be able to create an account if they have passed validation of all the fields described in REGISTRATION PAGE section
  • if validation is failed -> the input field will be shown in error-state and error message will be shown below the field.
  • Error message text (Indonesia site): You must be 18 or above years old to create an account
  • Error message text (Pakistan site): Please enter a valid CNIC number to proceed
  • Error message text won’t be manageable in admin panel
  1. This National ID field is also required to fill in during the SOCIAL LOGIN process.
  2. After user submit the registration:
  • The National ID will be stored in the User's Profile.
  • Admin is able to see and update the National ID from admin panel

VALIDATION LOGIC:

  • Indonesia site will apply KIP ID validation logic. Validation logic of KIP ID will be consistent as described in AGE VERIFICATION BASED ON KTP ID section
  • Pakistan site will apply CNIC ID validation logic. Validation logic of CNIC ID will be only length and quantity of symbols verification:
  • 13 digit number
  • Only number digits, no special character or alphabets
  • First Digit can be between 1-7
    e.g.
    Valid : 3770112431808
    Invalid : 8770112431823 or 377011243100

  1. On Account Information page:
  1. For users who have validated their National ID
  • Users are able to see the National ID that has been validated.
    The National ID field will be restricted for editing, user is not able to edit the National ID once it has been verified (field’s edit restriction is achieved by frontend programming, there will be no validation from backend if the field is edited or not from the access of Account Information page)
  • For Indonesian users, they will also see a new attribute 'Age Verified' with a ticked flag displayed under the ‘date of birth’ field. The ‘Age Verified’ field is not editable by users.
  1. For users who haven’t validated their National ID
  • Users will see ‘National ID’ field and have to input and validate their National ID when users try to update their profile, the behaviour is consistent as described in #1 Registration page section

  1. On Checkout page:
  1. Guest users and registered users without National ID stored
  • will see a National ID block with the following elements above the cost summary block
  • Title: Validate National ID (It is mandatory to place an order)
  • ‘Enter the National ID’ placeholder in text input field
  • Validate button
  • have to enter their National ID before they can place an order.
  • upon clicking on the ‘Validate’ button, validation of the data submitted in the National ID text input field will be performed.
  • validation logic will be hardcoded and not manageable
  • if validation is passed ->  
  • users will see the validation passed message in green (the styling is consistent as applied promo code, but without a delete button):
    National ID is validated
    National ID number (e.g. 3173075105820005)
  • when the National ID is validated and applied, users won’t be able to see the input field anymore to edit it.
  • If validation is failed -> the input field will be shown in error-state and error message will be shown below the field.
  • Error message text (Indonesia site): You must be 18 or above years old to place an order
  • Error message text (Pakistan site): Please enter a valid National ID to proceed
  • Error message text won’t be manageable in admin panel
  • if the users click on the ‘place an order’ button without inputting a National ID, the behaviour will be the same as validation is failed.
  1. Registered and Logged in user with stored National ID:
  • The National ID block will not be shown during the checkout page for registered & logged in users who have National ID stored in their profile.
  1. After user place an order:
  • The National ID will be stored on order level, admin can see the National ID in admin panel > view order details page.
  • Validated National ID will be stored into registered users’ profile, users can see the National ID in Account Information page but can’t edit it.
  • User won’t be able to see the National ID in their order details page
  • National ID won’t be displayed in any sales emails (i.e. order confirmation, order update, new shipment, shipment update, new invoices, invoice update emails) that are sent to the user.


Assumption:

  • The National ID won’t be sent to aCommerce, if aCommerce needs the National ID for fulfillment, they will need to do it separately offline.
  • Guest users will need to validate the National ID upon each Order Placement.
  • Age Verified field will only be applicable in Indonesia site, it is not required in Pakistan site.

  1. MAGENTO 2 & DIGISIGN INTEGRATION SPECIFICATION

GLOSSARY:

Term

Short Term

Description

Magento 2 Commerce platform

M2

Magento 2 Commerce platform used for the BAT Velo Indonesia storefront

Signature verification API

Digisign API

The interface of the Digisign platform, which wants to check the validity of user data

LUFT

LUFT

eWave headless commerce framework for Velo Indonesia storefront

INTEGRATION SCHEME:

SECURITY & AUTHORIZATION:

A header for request

Key

Value

Content-Type

application/json

Authorization

Bearer < token>

‘DATA VERIFICATION’ EVENT - REQUEST STRUCTURE:

Implementer

eWave

Endpoint System

Digisign.id

SystemTrigger

Real-time, on: customer registration, account update, order creation

Protocol

HTTPS

Method

POST

Security

Bearer <token>

Endpoint Service URL

https://apivrf.tandatanganku.com

URI

/data_verification.html

Communication Type

Synchronous

Expected Response

User verification data

Online Documentation

 Verification API document

Parameters

Required

Format

Description

nik

Y

String

KTP ID value

nama

Y

String

First name + Last name of the user

tempat_lahir

Y

String

N/A (Place of birth)

tanggal_lahir

Y

File

N/A (Date of birth (dd-MM-yyyy))

Example:

POST /customers/validateCreate HTTP/1.1

Content-Type: application/json

Authorization: Bearer <token>

{

    "nik": "3174061409910195",

    "nama": "Japutra Tedja",

    "tempat_lahir":"",

    "tanggal_lahir":""

}

DATA VERIFICATION EVENT - RESPONSE REQUIREMENTS:

Code

Content

Description

200

Type

Success

Description

Successful, created and validated if business

Content

Accepted: application/json

Type: Object

Items: customerCreation

Example

{

  "timestamp":1553155978,

  "status":200,

  "error":"",

  "message":"success",

  "data":{"name":true,"birthplace":true,"birthdate":true,"address":"JL.FL *MB*Y*N 4B"}

}

204

Type

No content

Description

The server has fulfilled the request but does not need to return an entity-body

Content

Accepted: application/json

Type: object

403

Type

Unauthorized

Description

Request forbidden by administrative rules.

  1. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

GENERAL CONFIGURATION:

The following configurations are to be set up in admin panel:

Stores > Configuration > Customers > Age verification:

  • Digisign API verification:
  • Enable Digisign API verification - Yes/No
    (set up on the store level)

INTEGRATION TRIGGERS:

The trigger to start the check process is:

  1. clicking the "Place order" button (Checkout) when the following conditions are met:
  1. A user does not have a "Age verified" mark
  2. A guest has passed the validation of the shipping address and KTP fields
  1. clicking the “Save changes” button (My account - Account information page), after the user has changed their personal info (name, national ID).

  • Logged in user:

  • Guest:

ASSUMPTIONS AND CONSTRAINTS:

  1. Username is defined as [First Name] + [Last Name]
  2. A new “HAV Query Results” table for storing data received from the API will be created on the back-end side
  3. All unsuccessful age verification attempts, as well as successful attempts for guests, will be recorded in the HAV Query Results table
  4. After the third unsuccessful Verification attempt (200 Name = False, 204) user activity will be blocked. To continue the purchase, they will need to contact the support. The corresponding error will be displayed when trying to place
  5. Errors returned by DigiSign will be displayed in the same wording in which they were received

    When the user tries to add a prize item (400 points) to the basket

    When the user tries to add a prize item (140 points) to the basket
    Then the item is successfully added

    Then the item is successfully added

    When the user tries to add another one prize item (280 + 140 points)
    Or  increase the prize item quantity in the basket to three or more
    Then they see the error message: “    Sorry, you don't have enough reward points”
  1. A prize product does not increase the total/subtotal value of the basket

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-ll-0162-1

 As a system, I want to calculate the date of birth of a user by his KTP ID

BAT-ll-0162-2

As a user, I want the Date of birth field to be filled in automatically so that I don't have to enter the same information twice when registering

DATE OF BIRTH CALCULATION ALGORITHM:

  • Indonesian KTP ID consists of 16 digits (3174096112900001)
    The feature should extract digits 7 through 12 inclusive (317409    6112900001) where:
  • 61 - day
  • 12 - month
  • 90 - year
  • if the “day” first digit > 3 (female identifier), the system should subtract 40 to get the real day of birth (61 - 40 = 21)
  • we assume that people up to 99 years old can buy BAT products
    2021-99 = 19    22
  • if the year of birth in the KTP ID is 23 or more, it means that it is 1923 - 1999
  • if the year of birth in the KTP ID is 22 or less, it means 2000-2022
  • the system sends the result of calculations to the front-end as a value of the "date" type
    611290 ->     21.12.1990

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Registration page
  1. After the user has entered a valid KTP ID and went to the next input field or clicked "create account", the date of birth extraction should be performed
  2. The extracting value must be filled in the “Date of birth” field.
  3. The Date of Birth age validation (over 18 years old, [BAT-II-0029] HARD AGE VERIFICATION (APPROVED)) should remain enabled:
  • validation will occur immediately after the DoB field is automatically filled in (AS IS)


  1. Guest Checkout page
  1. Just before the [BAT-II-0064] CONSUMER AGE VERIFICATION USING API PROVIDER, date of birth extraction should be performed
  2. The result of extraction is sent by the system as part of the Digisign API request

ID

USER STORY

GLO-US020-1

As a system, I want to check the validity of the entered personal data via 3rd party api integration

GLO-US020-2

As a site admin, I want the user's age to be checked at the time before order placing through the API request

GLO-US020-3

As a site admin, I want people under the age of 21 not to be able to purchase GLO

GLO-US020-4

As a user, I want to see a popup with age verification form, asking me to upload my ID Card for hard age verification when I go to registration page

GLO-US020-5

As a user, I want to see my “First Name”, “Last Name”, “Date of Birth” will be pre-filled into the registration page if I pass the hard age verification

GLO-US020-6

As a sysm, I want “First Name”, “Last Name” is editable, but “Date of Birth” is blocked for editing while registration

GLO-US020-7

As a system, I want  “First Name”, “Last Name”, “Date of Birth”  is blocked for manual changes on user’s my profile page

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. To register an account users need to confirm their own age.
  2. On the registration page,  a popup with age verification form will open over the registration page where user has to add own ID card image
  3. The validation form consists of the following elements::
  1. Dropdown with document type selection
  • The original list of document types will be hardcoded.
  • The admin will be able to select the types displayed in the dropdown on the storefront via the admin panel
  1. Image input field
  • By clicking on the field, a native system interface for working with files will open, where users can select an image and confirm their choice
  • [Mobile] for mobile devices, it will be also possible to take a photo directly from the registration page
  1. Explanatory text information (what to do, why to do it, what image formats are supported, is it secure)
  2. Upon clicking on the cancel button, user will be returned from the registration page to the previous page viewed
  3. Upon clicking “Submit” button after image is fully loaded, it is transferred to the BE side and a request to the Azure Computer Vision Service is occur
  • API as per M2 - Azure Computer Vision Integration Specification
  • based on the Response obtained, further age verification is carried out
  1. After user’s age is validated, username (“First name“, “Last name“) and “Date of Birth“ from Card Data (ID proof) will be captured and auto-filled into the registration page
  1. After passing the validation and closing the popup, a block with explanatory info  should appear on the registration page
  1. The block consists of 4 lines:
  • ‘Please check the name is recognized correctly’
  • [Recognized name]
  • ‘Re-verification can be done by clicking here’
  • ‘If the name was filled in incorrectly, you can fix it in in the fields below:’
  1. When a guest clicks on the "click here" link, a popup with a verification form appears
  1. Username (“First name“, “Last name“) are editable, but “Date of Birth“ will be blocked for manual changes while registration
  2. Upon clicking the ‘Create Account’ button on the registration page after the users fill in all the required information, the system will validate again whether the username (“First Name”, “Last Name”) is matched with Card Data. Notification message will appear if username is not matched with Card Data, user can’t proceed to create the account
    ‘    Profile name does not match card data, please check your details’

Validation Logic on username with the Card Data:
In case OCR can't identify the first name/last name from the Card Data, due to no placeholder on First/Last Name, validation will be passed if first name and last name can be identified as a part of the name from the Card Data.

  1. After 5 unsuccessful attempts, a guest can no longer create an account in the current session
  1. At the next attempt to create an account, an error message should appear:
    “    Sign up attempts are exceeded. Please contact us to complete your registration”
  2. When a guest clicks on ‘Contact us’ link, they go to the relevant ‘Contact Us’ page
  1. After the user successfully completes the registration of an account, or leaves the page, the uploaded image is deleted
  2. The customer attributes '”First name”, “Last name”, “Date of Birth” will be blocked from manual changes on user’s My Profile page

RESPONSE

DETAILS

200

  1. Depending on the selected document type, the appropriate Json parsing method will be applied
    (    different documents will have a different JSON response structure. We will prepare an algorithm for extracting the name and date of birth based on the resulting structure for each doc type separately)
  2. Success is considered a situation when:
  • uploaded card matches the selected card type
  • document country is Philippines
  • ‘Current date’ - ‘Date of Birth’  > 21 year (662,695,992 sec)
  1. If verification is successful, then:
  • Date of birth from the document is filled in the "date of birth" customer attribute
  • Username (“First name”, “Last name”) from the document is filled in the “First name”, “Last name” customer attribute
  • A customer account is created
  • The user gets 'Age verified' mark (Yes/No)
  • Document Type will be stored in user’s profile in DB, but not visible in storefront
  • ID Number (Masked) will be stored in user’s profile in DB, but not visible in the storefront
  1. ‘The type of card does not match the selected one, please choose a different type, or use the corresponding card photo’
    error message should appears If the card type does not match the selected
  2. ‘Profile name does not match card data, please check your details’
    notification message should appears If the username on the site does not match with the card data
  3. ‘According to the data received, you are less than 21 years old. The account cannot be created’
    error message should appears If ‘Current date’ - Date of Birth <= 21 year (662,695,992 sec)

400

‘Bad Request. Please try another photo or contact support’ error message is displayed

415

Unsupported media. Please try another photo or contact support' error message is displayed

500

‘Internal server error. Please try again 5 minutes later or contact support’ error message is displayed


ASSUMPTIONS AND CONSTRAINTS:

  • Testing will be conducted using publicly available photographs of ID cards available on the Internet.

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Admin should be able to generate a report that will include the following columns:
  1. Order # - a unique number of an Order that has been assigned to the order entity inside the Magento system.
  2. Customer name
  3. Customer ID - a unique number of a Customer that has been assigned to the customer entity inside the Magento system. For guest users it could be N/A or null.
  4. Purchased On - a date when Order has been recorded in the Magento system.
  5. Status - a current Order Status in the Magento system.
  6. Payment Method - a method that was used on the platform during Order placement
  7. CNIC # - The value provided during the Order placement for a guest user or CNIC number saved as an attribute in the Customer profile for logged in users
  8. Qty Ordered
  9. Discount
  10. Shipping
  11. Grand Total
  12. Products - a name of the product and quantity per product line that were purchased with this Order (Product or Bundle)
  1. Admin should be able to export the generated report in .csv format

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0124-US1

As a admin user, I want to import a .csv file of a provided format to update Orders in Magento in bulk

BUSINESS REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Fulfillers will be consolidating orders for update in a file according to the format described below
  2. Each market will have their separate file, so upon upload Orders in the file will belong to only one website
  3. Partial Shipment or Partial Invoicing will not be supported via bulk upload, admin will update such orders manually in admin panel using Orders grid
  4. All other statuses, except from complete, like canceled or holded, will be updated manually and not expected to be used for bulk upload

IMPORT BEHAVIOR REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Admin should be able to update existing in Magento orders in bulk via admin panel
  2. Admin should be able to select a file, that will consist of all Orders that we need to update and import it
  3. Admin should be able to see information about any issues occurred during update (for example, order# skipped summary, general errors)

IMPORT FILE REQUIREMENTS:

  1. File format is to be .csv
  2. File columns should include:
  1. Order#
  2. Order Status
  3. Order Comment (optional)
  4. Carrier (optional)
  5. Title (optional)
  6. Tracking# (optional)

IMPORT FILE DATA:

FILE COLUMN

DATA SAMPLE

COMMENTS

increment_id

BATDEVSO000000001

status

complete

status_history_prefix_comment

this order was delivered by a fulfiller

if blank, should have no value upon upload

if not blank, should be added to the order comment, a customer should have no visibility of this comment. it’s only for internal purposes and only visible in the admin panel on order details page

shipment_track_prefix_carrier_code

Custom Value

if blank, should be defaulted to Custom Value

shipment_track_prefix_title

Best Carrier

if blank, should have no value upon upload

shipment_track_prefix_track_number

TR3453BN

if blank, should have no value upon upload

store_id

pakistan_store

added to improve the performance of the upload, can be skipped

IMPORT SCENARIOS REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Order No is not matching to any existing Order records in Magento DB -> Order should be skipped, no new Order creation is expected, information about this Order is to be displayed to the admin after update is finished
  2. Order Status is complete in the imported file, but current status is pending -> Order is to be automatically invoiced and shipped, corresponding transactional emails are to be sent to the customer email address
  3. If  Order Comment, Carrier, Title or Tracking# are blank, this will not affect the update, this data is optional
  4. One shipment will have only one tracking number

EXPORT REQUIREMENTS:

No Order export functionality is required.

As an admin user, I want cron job to be configured according to the business needs

As an admin user, I want Orders to be canceled in Magento on configured schedule and conditions

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  • Admin should be able to set up the following:
  • enable/disable cron job on website scope level
  • set cron schedule
  • Should be a cron-like expression.
  • Example: 59 23 * * * , will trigger cron every day at 23:59
  • set Order Status, to filter orders by
  • multi-select, will show all Order Statuses that are applicable to the web-site
  • Example: if Pending Order Status is selected and there is an Order that matches all other filters, this Order will be affected by cron job
  • set Payment Method, to filter orders by
  • multi-select, will show all Payment Methods that are enabled for the web-site
  • Currently enabled payment methods for Indonesia:
  • Virtual Account Transfer/Instant payments (EsPay)
  • Cash on Delivery
  • Example: if Virtual Account Transfer/Instant payments payment method is selected and there is an Order that matches all other filters, this Order will be affected by cron job
  • set Order expiration time, to filter orders by
  • input field, validation: accepts integers only
  • expiration time will be set in hours
  • expiration time should be calculated from Order Date
  • Example: if 24 is set as Order expiration time, and there is an Order that was placed 24hours ago or more, and this Order matches all other filters, this Order will be affected by cron job
  • There will be only one cron job set at a time, no ability to set multiple cron jobs on different schedule
  • All Orders that are matching the criteria of the cron configuration will be affected on the set cron schedule in the following way:
  • Order Status to be assigned -> Canceled
  • No email will be sent about order status change
  • reserved stock by this Order will be released for products (default Magento behavior)

USER STORY

BAT-II-0080-US1

As a site admin, I want to combine several separate coupons into one tiered promo codel

BAT-II-0080-US2

As a user, when entering a coupon, I want to receive different discounts, depending on the conditions I have fulfilled in the shopping cart

BAT-II-0080-US3

As a site admin I want be able to assign products as free promo items

BAT-II-0080-US3

As a user, I want to be able to receive a promo item or a free gift in my order

All the features of this section do not change the current functionality of cart price rules, but only expand its capabilities

  1. TIERED COUPONS

A third party module will be used to meet the current need:
https://marketplace.magento.com/mexbs-module-tieredcoupon.html

Tiered coupons userguide:
https://marketplace.magento.com/media/catalog/product/mexbs-module-tieredcoupon-1-1-4-ce/user_guides.pdf

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. A new menu item will be added in BO:
                Marketing > Tiered Coupons
  2. The site administrator will be able to add new tiered coupons
  1. A list of all price rules (using coupon) must be available for selection in a tiered coupon
  2. The admin should be able to generate batch of promo codes automatically
  1. When user enter a tier coupon, the cart price rule, the conditions of which were fulfilled in the order, will be triggered
  2. Except for grouping several promotional codes into one coupon, the module does not affect the operation of the cart rules in any way.
  3. Tiered coupons will not be visible in the Coupon Wallet

  1. FREE GIFTS

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. A new menu item will be added in BO:
                Stores > Configuration > Ewave > Free Gift
  1. This area will be used to define the basic settings (default settings) of using the functionality
  1. The following options will be added to the cart price rules actions:
  1. Free promo items with products
  2. Free promo items for the whole cart
  3. The same free product
  4. Free promo items for every $X
  5. For every X get Y cheapest products as free promo items
  1. Depending on the option chosen, the site admin will be able to:
  1. select simple products as promo items by SKU
  2. specify whether the promo product will be automatically added to the cart, or manually from the pop-up on the Cart page
  3. determine the quantity of promo item and the frequency of its provision
  4. hide promo item ‘for the whole cart' on the storefront. The added promo product will be visible in the order only in the admin panel
  5. Specify Free Gift message in the Cart
  1. The site admin will be able to hide free item price on the cart and minicart (wording instead of “$0.00”)
  2. The promol items will not affect the shipping cost, which depends on the number of items in the cart

ASSUMPTIONS AND CONSTRAINTS:

  1. The display of additional blocks and descriptions of promo products on the PDP for the "Free promo items with products" action is beyond the scope of works

BAT-II-0171-US2

"BAT_Storelocator" package from the global code repository is to be used.

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  • Admin is able to import stores in admin panel (Content > Store Locator > Import)
  • Admin is able to customize store marker in Magento Configuration
  • Store locator icon is displayed in the main navigation next to Sign in option (Desktop)
  • Find in store option is displayed above push notification switcher in the menu (Mobile)
  • User will be able to search for a location:
  • Once user starts typing dropdown with the list of suggestions is shown (powered by Google)
  • User is able to use current location for search 
  • If browser restrictions are applied user will be asked to change browser settings
  • Once location is selected the list of stores is displayed:
  • A store card shows:
  • Name (comes from Magento)
  • Address (comes from Magento)
  • Distance (provided by Google map)
  • ‘Get directions’ button
  • The first store in the list is highlighted with a bold frame but not considered as a selected one therefor store information is not be displayed on the map nearby the relevant store marker
  • Once user clicks a specific store item in the list:
  • The card is highlighted with a bold frame
  • A pop up with the store name and address is displayed on the map nearby the relevant store marker
  • The colour of the store marker is changed
  • Once user clicks a specific store marker on the map:
  • The respective card in the list is not highlighted with a bold frame, previous selection stays as is
  • A pop up with the store name and address is displayed on the map nearby the relevant store marker
  • The colour of the store marker is changed
  • The marks with the number of stores on the map should change their colour while zooming based on the following rules:
  • a mark should be green if the number of stores is less than 10
  • a mark should be purple if the number of stores is equal or more than 10 and less than 20
  • a mark should be blue if the number of stores is equal or more than 20
  • Once user clicks ‘Get directions’ button a new tab with Google map is opened with the direction to the selected store

ASSUMPTIONS:

  1. Store locator module does not allow setting permissions for importing the list of stores, that means that an admin of any store is able to import the list of stores for any website no matter what scope he is assigned to.
  2. The list of already imported stores is scope specific - abmin will be able to see the list of stores in BE referring to his scope only.

USER STORY

BAT-II-0251US1

As an admin I want DOB to be captured during guest checkout

BAT-II-0251US2

As an admin I want an order to be placed only for valid age customers

BAT-II-0251US3

As an admin I want DOB to be saved on the order level

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  3. User is not able to proceed with the checkout unless eligible DOB is provided.
  4. DOB is to be recorded on the order level, so a new attribute date_of_birth is to be added in the BE for an order

Note: For GLO-IND, GLO-PH DOB feature should be disabled in BE as guest checkout is not allowed for these markets
