  1. [BAT-II-0252] INTEGRATION TO CHECKOUT.COM (KSA) (APPROVED)

FEATURE HIGHLIGHTS:

AREAS

SUMMARY

Is this a new Feature or a Change of existing Feature?

New Feature

What is the Business Need behind this Feature implementation?

Payment Gateway for KSA

Is this feature applied to all resolutions?

Yes

Does this Feature require change in the admin panel?

Yes

Are there any dependencies with other Features?

No

Are there any dependencies with Integrations or 3rd party systems?

Yes, checkout.com

Applicable for both logged in and guest users?

No (applicable for admin user only)

Market or Core?

Market

Enabled for Markets

KSA

FEATURE SCOPE:

  • EWAVE to enable the following module: Checkout.com
  • check and activate according to the provided instructions in Magento 2 - Docs (checkout.com)
  • All Checkout and Order Success Page functionality, All transactional emails that are currently being sent from Magento will remain as is and won’t be changed.
  • All configuration within checkout.com platform will not be in scope for this feature for EWAVE

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

Below are the set of configurations to be applied to Magento (STORES > Configuration-> Web-site scope)

  • Sales > Payment Methods > Configuration > checkout.com > configuration

  • Global Settings
  • Enable Module - Yes
  • Default Active Method - TBC
  • Payment Action - Authorize and Capture
  • Capture Time - 0.02 (Specify the number of hours before capture. Ex: 1.5 for capture after 1h30. For performance reasons, there is a minimum delay of 0.02 (72 seconds).)
  • Enable Dynamic Descriptor: No
  • Enable Webhook Table: Yes (This enables webhooks to be logged to a dedicated table to improve traceability for when webhook events are received.
  • Enable Webhook Table Clean: No
  • Order Settings
  • Action on Failed Payment - Cancel the order  (Select the action that should be taken for orders with failed payments.)
  • Order confirmation email - Authorize and Capture (Defines if the order confirmation email should be sent after successful payment authorisation or payment capture.)
  • Authorization Order Status - Pending Payment  (the status that should be used for orders with successful payment authorisation.)
  • Capture Order Status - Processing (the status that should be used for orders with successful payment capture.)
  • Void Order Status - Canceled (the status that should be used for orders with successful payment void.)
  • Partial Refund Order Status - Closed ( the status that should be used for orders with successful payment partial refund.)
  • Flagged Order Status - Suspected Fraud  (the status that should be used for flagged orders.)
  • Account Settings (Following keys should be provided by BAT, by retrieving from checkout.com account)
  • Secret Key
  • Public Key
  • Private Shared Key
  • Sandbox account
  • URL: https://sandbox.checkout.com/dashboard
  • Username: tarek_albsat@bat.com         
  • Password: P@ssw0rd

        

Payment Methods

  • only Credit Card Payments should be enabled

                Card Payments configuration:

  • Payment Option Title - TBC (this is associated with ‘Default Active Method’ in Global Settings)
  • Enable Card Payments - Yes
  • Language Fallback - English
  • Display Card Icons - Yes
  • Card Icons - Assumption is only Visa and Mastercard (and MADA) should be enabled and tested; also both Credit and Debit cards are required to be covered.
  • Visa
  • Mastercard
  • American Express
  • Diners Club International
  • Discover
  • JCB
  • Use 3D Secure - Yes
  • Save Card Option - No
  • Enable MADA BIN Check: Yes  (Add a flag to the charge request if the payment card is MADA. Enabling the MADA feature will force auto capture and 3D Secure for all MADA payment requests.)
  • Payment form layout: Single iframe / Multiple iframe (to be recommended by Dev)

Other Payment Methods should not be enabled or configured

  • Alternative Payments
  • Apple Pay Payments
  • Google Pay Payments
  • Saved Card Payments
  • MOTO Payments

Integration Requirement

  • Currently OpenCart Storefront integration is using the Card Payments with Frames.js. Payment iFrame is expected to insert in storefront. Should follow the same integration in M2.
  • Frames integration approach should be implemented based on the checkout.com documentation
  • Frontend: Along with insert iframe on Frontend, it will require to build a new payment gateway UI component on LUFT
  • Backend: It will require extend current Magento 2 module (GraphQL part)

Assumption

  • Payment Methods display is within iframe
  • Styling will be only able to be implemented within iframe, it will be managed on checkout.com Team
  • Styling of section within iframe is not included in this feature
  • if its styling is required to be consistent with existing storefront , related styling codes is required to build and share from eWave with checkout.com for their handling
  • and additional estimate would be required

PH-GLO

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0127-US1

As an admin, I want to enable/disable paynamics payment gateway on the website level scope

BAT-II-0127-US2

As an admin, I want to configure paynamics payment gateway specifically for my website

BAT-II-0127-US3

As a user I want to be able to select a payment with paynamics payment gateway during checkout

MODULES:

A third party module will be used to meet the current need:

https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1AwdNjdY_0-1kQi5oSF1JxRrMhN5np5uz?usp=sharing

RPF integration model will be leveraged:

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1GIhL8OvZI3XFwiNVMTNdZRnJe_QaB9ap/view?usp=sharing 

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  • (Manageable from the admin panel list) - a user will be able to see a selection of enabled payment methods on the checkout page including currently used COD and all payment methods available via paynamics payment gateway
  • deprecated by requirements below - no additional logic about payment availability based on the address, amount and so on will be required.
  • additional logic required based on the Payment from Applicable Countries configuration is required to display payment methods related to paynamics payment gateway
  • if payment is not from allowed country, we will not show these payment methods
  • additional logic based on the Minimum Order Total and Maximum Order Total configuration is required to display payment methods related to paynamics payment gateway
  • if the order total is below or above the limit (including all additional charges and discounts), we will not show these payment methods

  • The list of payment methods to be used is as follows:
  • Credit Debit Card
  • Gcash
  • Coins
  • Alipay
  • WeChat Pay
  • Grabpay
  • an admin will be able to do the following:
  • enable/disable a specific payment method to be displayed to the user
  • update the payment method title to be displayed to the user
  • set the sequence to the payment method to be displayed to the user
  • Not required - add new payment methods on top of the specified list
  • Not required - manage payment method icon
  • a user will be able to select one of the available payment methods from the list
  • once a payment method belongs to the paynamics payment gateway, user will:
  • see the payment method being selected
  • see a note below that after Order Placement user will be redirected to another page to complete the payment
  • this text won’t be manageable in the admin panel and will be the same for any payment option that belongs to the paynamics payment gateway
  • T&C checkbox and text are not required to be placed under each payment method, this will stay as is per current implementation (text with links below Place Order button)

  • after user clicks place an Order button, all the validations are performed as normal and if successful, user will be redirected to the paynamics page to complete the payment
  •  the selected payment method will be displayed on paynamics payment gateway page (we will pass the selected on Magento side value via pmethod parameter)

Note: ewave won’t have any control over the page above, this page is fully hosted by paynamics team

  • Once the payment has been completed successfully on the paynamics payment gateway page, the Order record will be created in Magento db, the user will be redirected back to the Magento website and will see the Order Success page with corresponding Order No
  • If the payment was cancelled on paynamics payment gateway page, the user will be redirected back to back to Magento (pnx/ipn/result redirecting to checkout page) with a global message indicating that the Payment has been cancelled. The plugin currently does not have handling to restore the cart details.
  • If the payment has not been completed successfully, the user will be redirected back to Magento (pnx/ipn/result redirecting to checkout page) with a global message indicating that the Payment has failed with its corresponding reason. The plugin currently does not have handling to restore the cart details.
  • module will not support refund functionalities to be triggered on Magento side

NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  • module compatibility is to be refined thoroughly, as this module is for Magento Community Edition, and not Enterprise, so we need to make sure that all the required logic for us is supported by this payment gateway module
  • SEO impact caused by the redirection to a 3rd party hosted page is being acknowledged and no actions are required for now for additional tracking
  • data formats will stay as per current implementation on the website, no need to update
  • For example, Phone Number format required by paynamics is +xxx(yyy)zzz-zzzz, where xxx - country code, yyy - operator code, zzz-zzzz number. On the website side the phone number will be collected as is now, and no additional changes required since confirmed with paynamics team that there is no validation on their side

MODULE CONFIGURATION REQUIREMENTS:

Scope: Glo-PH website

Stores -> Configuration -> Sales -> Payment Methods -> Paynamics Payment Gateway

  • Enabled - Yes 
  • Title - Paynamics
  • Sort Order - 2
  • Payment from Applicable Countries - Specific Countries 
  • Payment from Specific Countries - Philippines 
  • Minimum Order Total - blank
  • Maximum Order Total - blank
  • Mode - Test [will be set Live on production env at a confirmed live date]
  • Transaction Type - Sale [as recommended by paynamics team]
  • Test Merchant ID - 00000021072170B82A7B
  • Test Merchant Key - F6A78459A3BEB8C871C33EAC80224C38
  • Test Payment URL - https://testpti.payserv.net/webpayment/Default.aspx
  • Live Merchant ID - [will be provided at a later stage]
  • Live Merchant Key - [will be provided at a later stage]
  • Live Payment URL - [will be provided at a later stage]
  • IP Address - will be added during development by dev team
  • Descriptor - TBC [Company name which appears on a billing statement]
  • Terms and Conditions URL - blank
  • Logo URL - will be added during development by dev team
  • Notification URL - blank [Callback URL where PAYGATE would POST base64 encoded xml notification update for their transaction or its final status. Leave empty to use default.]

PERMISSIONS CONFIGURATION REQUIREMENTS:

only PH-GLO admin and global admin should have permissions to see and update configurations of this module

  1. [DRAFT] [BAT-II-0269] USER LOGIN OPTION TO HAVE PHONE NUMBER IN ADDITION TO EMAIL ADDRESS

FEATURE HIGHLIGHTS:

AREAS

SUMMARY

Is this a new Feature or a Change of existing Feature?

Change

What is the Business Need behind this Feature implementation?

Some markets don’t use email addresses.

User should be able to log in using phone number instead of email address

Is this feature applied to all resolutions?

Yes

Does this Feature require change in the admin panel?

Yes

Are there any dependencies with other Features?

No

Are there any dependencies with Integrations or 3rd party systems?

Yes

Applicable for both logged in and guest users?

Both

Market or Core?

Core

Enabled for Markets

PAK-VELO

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0269-US1

As a user I want to be able to login using my email or phone number on Login and Checkout Pages

BAT-II-0269-US2

As a user I want be able to request and use confirmation code instead of password to Log In with mobile phone

BAT-II-0269-US3

As an Admin I want to be able to enable/disable Login via Mobile Phone Extension

BAT-II-0269-US4

As an Admin I want to be able to enable/disable guest to login using SMS confirmation code

BAT-II-0269-US5

As an Admin I want a mobile phone number to be unique for each customer

BAT-II-0269-US6

As an Admin I want a mobile phone number to be verified during registration with OTP code sent via SMS

MODULES

Customer Login by Phone LEGO Module is to be reused

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

Enable Login via Mobile Phone is set to Yes

  1. Admin is able to:
  1. Set up validation of phone number format -TBC if needed or we can just hardcode the country code like on registration page and don't use this setting at all
  2. Set up validation of phone number by store country or selected country list. - TBC if needed or we can just hardcode the country code like on registration page and don't use this setting at all
  1. Login flow:
  1. User is able to login with email or switch the option and enter a phone number provided during registration
  2. Login with email is selected by default
  3. Copy is updated to ‘If you are registered user, please enter your email or phone number and password.’
  4. If ‘Login with mobile’ is clicked:
  1. Phone number field is displayed instead of email field
  2. ‘Login with mobile’ copy is replaced with ‘Login with email’. User is able to switch back to email
  3. User needs to provide mobile number and password
  4. Enable Country Mobile Phone Validation is set to Yes: TBC if needed or we can just hardcode the country code like on registration page and don't use this setting at all
  1. When user starts typing mobile number then greyed out country code mask is displayed (similar to registration flow)
  2. Otherwise user can enter any phone number
  1. If the phone number or/and password provided is not correct or does not exist error message is displayed ‘Wrong phone number or password’ when user clicks Login
  1. Registration flow on the storefront:
  1. Once the user provides all the details and clicks ‘Register’ a check is to be done whether the phone number is unique or not.
  1. If the phone number exists, is valid and unique:
  1. A pop up will be displayed where the Customer will be able to enter Confirmation Code AND and a button 'Request confirmation code' and 'Confirm'
  2. Once user clicks 'Request confirmation code' button OTP (confirmation code) will be sent by SMS provider
  3. 'Request confirmation code' button should become unavailable for the period of time, which is set in 'Confirmation Code Request Frequency'
  4. Countdown timer should appear when the user presses 'Request confirmation code' button. 'Request confirmation code' button should become disabled until this time set in 'Confirmation Code Request Frequency' run out.
  5. After Customer enters correct received code, and clicks ‘Confirm’ the pop up will be closed and success toast message is displayed notifying customer that the phone number has been confirmed
  6. Once phone number is confirmed a new attribute in M2 phone_is_confirmed should be set to Yes.
  7. If entered confirmation code is wrong or expiration time within 'Confirmation Code Expiration Time' setting run out - message, set in 'Invalid Code Message' should be displayed
  8. Customers should not be able to use the same code more than one time. Confirmation code should automatically become expired after successful confirmation.
  9. If integration error occurs - the system should log errors and show an error message, manageable in 'Integration Error Message' setting.
  1. If there is already an existing customer with the same phone number, an error message is to be displayed ‘A customer with the same phone number already exists in an associated website.’
  1. Change phone number on the account page:
  1. Once the user changes a phone number on the account details page a check is to be done whether the phone number is unique or not.
  2. If there is already an existing customer with the same phone number, an error message is to be displayed ‘A customer with the same phone number already exists in an associated website.’

Enable LogIn with SMS Confirmation Code is set to Yes (mandatory once Login via Mobile Phone module is enabled)

  1. Admin is be able to:
  1. select the SMS Provider
  2. specify a message to display, in case the customer will enter invalid SMS confirmation code  
  3. specify a message to display for the Customer, in case of integration error occurs  
  4. specify confirmation code expiration time in seconds
  5. specify frequency in seconds for repeated confirmation code request
  1. Login flow:
  1. 'Request one-time password' button is available below the 'Password' field
  2. Once user enters phone number and clicks ‘Request one-time password’:
  1. The system checks validity of the phone number
  2. If the phone is valid and exists:
  1. Textfield should appear, where the Customer will be able to enter Confirmation Code AND and a button 'Login with confirmation code'
  2. System should generate a confirmation code in accordance with the settings of the Provider, selected in the 'Provider' settings and sent by selected Provider to the Customer
  3. 'Request confirmation code' button should become unavailable for the period of time, which is set in 'Confirmation Code Request Frequency'
  4. Countdown timer should appear when the user presses 'Request confirmation code' button. 'Request confirmation code' button should become disabled until this time set in 'Confirmation Code Request Frequency' run out.
  5. After Customer enters correct received code, and clicks ‘Login with confirmation code’ he should be logged in to the website
  6. If entered confirmation code is wrong or expiration time within 'Confirmation Code Expiration Time' setting run out - message, set in 'Invalid Code Message' should be displayed
  7. Customers should not be able to register with the same code more than one time. Confirmation code should automatically become expired after successful login.
  8. If integration error occurs - the system should log errors and show an error message, manageable in 'Integration Error Message' setting.

  2. Admin is able to - TBC:
  1. specify confirmation code length, excluding prefix, suffix, separators.
  2. specify confirmation code format.
  3. specify a text message to be sent with a code.
  4. any other settings required

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0276-US1

As an admin I want the orders to be posted from M2 to Aramex for further fulfillment

BAT-II-0276-US2

As an admin I want the order statuses to be updated in M2 based on the information received from Aramex

BAT-II-0276-US3

As an admin I want the shipment details to be received from Aramex

BAT-II-0276-US4

As an admin I want new order statuses to be added in M2 to reflect Aramex ones

BAT-II-0276-US5

As an admin I want an invoice to be auto created when the orders get ‘Complete’ state (both for online and COD payment methods)

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:

  1. Admin should be able to enable/disable Aramex integration on store level
  2. Once integration is enabled the setting ‘Enable Invoice auto creation on delivery date’ should be available:
  1. A setting will change the logic when invoice is auto created:
  1.  It will disable invoice auto creation when payment is done and enable invoice auto creation when the order state is ‘Complete’ (once it’s delivered).
  2. Valid both for for online and COD payment methods
  3. No need to create invoices manually for COD orders
  4. The date of invoice should be the date of delivery (when status changed to complete)
  1. Orders should be sent from M2 to Aramex once they are paid (for online payment methods) or created (for COD payment method)
  2. Order status updates should be sent by Aramex to M2 once the status is changed in WMS
  3. Shipment updates should be sent by Aramex to M2 once order is ready for delivery
  4. New statuses should be added in M2 and mapped to processing[Processing] state to reflect Aramex statuses:
  1. Did Not Allocate
  2. Part Allocated
  3. Part Released
  4. Part Picked
  1. All transactions from M2 to WMS and from WMS to M2 should be logged
  2. Integration between M2 and Aramex should done as per Aramex Integration Specification

  1. DATA MIGRATION PLAN (APPROVED)

No data is supposed to be migrated. No 301 redirects set-up is required.

  1. ERROR MANAGEMENT (APPROVED)

By default Magento application errors and exceptions will be logged in exception.log file. Any unhandled exceptions will be recorded as a  report file.

Each integration has different requirements on the actions that Magento needs to perform in an error event (ex: Sending an email to a given email addresses). Requirements on the Error Management of the integrations will be described in the corresponding Integration Specification documents.

Any Magento Rest API errors will be included in the response body. So the entity that calls the Magento Rest API needs to handle the returning error and do necessary actions.

  1. SECURITY (APPROVED)

  • HTTPS connection should be used entirely for all storefront on all environments.
  • Admin panel is to have custom admin URL path for production environment
  • Magento two-factor authentication (MFA) feature is to be enabled for production environment

BAT has not provided any additional requirements on security. In the development eWave will ensure common security requirements are in place and verified.

  1. SEARCH ENGINE (APPROVED)

Default Magento Search (MySQL) will be used for MVP.

  1. PRICING (APPROVED)

Price setting and changes to prices will be done through either manual importing of data or through the standard Magento Admin Interface.

  1. STOCK LEVELS (APPROVED)

Single stock inventory setup will be used. No MSI (Multi-Store Inventory) is considered in scope.

Product inventory setting and changes to product stock will be done through aCommerce integration. Details of this inventory integration will be described in the Integration Specification document.

  1. REPORTING (APPROVED)

Default Magento admin panel Reporting will be used for the MVP launch.

Detailed breakdown on the supported reports below:

  • Marketing - All reporting is supported
  • Sales - Not Supported: PayPal Settlement, Braintree Settlement
  • Customers - Not supported: Segments
  • Products - Not supported: Downloads
  • Private Sales - not supported

  1. H1,2,3 TAGS FOR PRODUCTS, CATEGORIES & CMS

H tags will be marked in accordance with eWave best practices:

  • Every page of the site must have the only one H1 meta tag formatted as text that has appropriate content (i.e. h1 on a category page = category name, h1 on the product page = product name).
  • The number of h2 and h3 meta tags is not limited, however, they should form the relevant and clear structure.

  1. OPEN GRAPH TAGS FOR PRODUCTS & CMS

Product Details and CMS pages will have set open graph tags in code for future users’ social networking posts.

  1. BREADCRUMBS

Breadcrumbs block on PLP according to the description in BREADCRUMBS BLOCK section.

  1. ROBOTS.TXT

  1. STAGING AND DEVELOPMENT INSTANCES

All pages are to be restricted from crawl via editing robots.txt or by adding "noindex, nofollow"

  1. PRODUCTION INSTANCE

Following pages should be restricted from crawl via editing robots.txt or by adding "noindex, follow":

/search

/cart/**

/account/**

/checkout/**

/admin/**

example: <meta name="robots" content="NOINDEX,FOLLOW"/>

  1. XML SITEMAP

Sitemap is to be created before launch, once all content pages are created and finalized. Sitemap should have the following URL: */sitemap.xml

Market or Core?

Core

Enabled for Markets
(VELO-ID, VELO-PAK, VELO-UAE, GLO-PH, GLO-ID)

All

HIGH LEVEL REQUIREMENTS COVERED BY THIS SECTION:

ID

USER STORY

BAT-II-0272-US1

As an admin I want full category path as part of the Product detail page URL

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

This feature will leverage on default configurations

Stores > Configuration > Catalog > Search Engine Optimization >

  • Use Categories Path for Product URLs: Yes
  • Generate Category/Product URL Rewrites: Yes
  • Create Permanent Redirect for URLs if URL Key Changed: Yes
  • Use Canonical Link Meta Tag for Categories: Yes
  • Use Canonical Link Meta Tag for Products: Yes

Pre-condition: above settings should be enabled

With “Use Categories Path for Product URLs: Yes”

If a user has clicked on the product from inside the PLP page, it will show the Category path inside the product URL on the PDP of this product.

  • Expected Product Detail Page URL to be in following format:

https://domainname/full-category-path(composed with url key)/productUrlKey

  • The full category path will also be dependent on which category the product is assigned to, e.g. when a product is assigned under a Lv2 category, expected URL is

https://domainname/Lv1-CategoryUrlKey/Lv2-CategoryUrlKey/productUrlKey.html

If a user has clicked on the product inside the SRP (search results page) or on a banner or anywhere outside of the category and navigated directly to the PDP, it won't show any Category path inside the product URL

  • Expected Product Detail Page URL to be in following format:

https://domainname/productUrlKey

With “Use Canonical Link Meta Tag for Products: Yes”

The canonical meta tag should be placed in the <head> in Product Page

Format: <link rel="canonical" href="{absolute canonical url}" />

Example: <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.discoverglo.com/ph/en/devices/glo-hyper-white.html" />

OR <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.discoverglo.com/ph/en/devices/glo-hyper-white" />

Note: having “.html” or not in suffix is depending on the configuration in Stores> Configuration > Catalog > Search Engine Optimization

  • Product URL suffix

With Use Canonical Link Meta Tag for Categories: Yes

The canonical meta tag should be placed in the <head> in Category Page

Format: <link rel="canonical" href="{absolute canonical url}" />

Example: <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.discoverglo.com/ph/en/devices" />

Note: having “.html” or not in suffix is depending on the configuration in Stores> Configuration > Catalog > Search Engine Optimization

  • Category URL suffix

Official Magento User Guide Canonical Meta Tag | Adobe Commerce 2.3 User Guide (magento.com)

Applicable for both logged in and guest users?

For guest users only

Market or Core?

Market

Enabled for Markets

IND

FEATURE SCOPE:

  • ewave to set up the snippet on all the environments according to the following instructions:
  • Basic script to track page views and link clicks - https://docs.meiro.io/books/meiro-events/page/how-to-deploy-meiro-events-on-the-website
  • Where you need to define the collector domain, here is the domain for BAT : me.bat.meiro.io
  • Please make sure to configure the user ID (this should be the unique ID that Magento assigns for logged-in users) as a custom payload in Pageview events: Configure Custom Payload - https://docs.meiro.io/books/meiro-events/page/events-how-to-pass-additional-data-into-page-view-event 
  • Contact Form Submission tracking script - https://docs.meiro.io/books/meiro-events/page/events-how-to-track-contact-forms-from-the-website 
  • This script must be implemented on all forms existing on the website.
  • Here is the list of forms and form fields which needs to be completed - please update this list as you implement the from tracking script and this will help us parse the form information correctly - https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1kJ5Qr_6TaZwzP-pzTqwV7NPlF3sChaT0kgdViB_Y8LM/edit?usp=sharing (note from Meiro team: additional forms are to be added to the list and confirmed with the client, whether we need to track them. For Column C - "Unique Form ID”, this can be anything set by the ewave team (as long as there’s no space) - we use this to query for all submissions to the same form. I added some form ID examples such as: registration_form, log_in, main_check_out. All the fields from the specified form are to be added to "Fields (Filled by Client)" (Column H))
  • Please make sure to configure the transaction ID (this should be the unique ID for each order made) as a custom dimension in all the forms (note from Meiro team: this is related to the instruction to configure transaction ID as a custom dimension to all the forms (as long as a transaction ID is present). By Transaction ID, we are referring to a unique ID assigned by Magento to identify individual transactions. The intention here is to tie the web behaviour & form submissions on Velo website, captured by Meiro events, with the purchase behaviour from Magento (for which we are getting unique ID for each transaction).
  • Deploy cookies sync script for The Trade Desk - https://docs.meiro.io/books/meiro-events/page/trade-desk-how-to-deploy-meiro-events-with-the-trade-desk-on-the-website

  1. GOOGLE TAG MANAGER (APPROVED)

GTM snippets are to be added to staging and production environments.

Snippets are provided here.

  1. [PIII] PERFORMANCE ENHANCEMENT

  1. [BAT-II-0224] SVG Sprite

FEATURE SCOPE:

  • all SVG front-end icons is to be packed into a single sprite file
  • when loading the page, the system should make one request to a pre-prepared sprite and not separate requests for each new icon
  • Whenever the front-end build of the website is updated, the SVG sprite file must be updated too

  1. [BAT-II-0245] Persisted queries

FEATURE SCOPE:

  • The Persisted Query function is to be enabled on both the BE and FE side.
  • GET method will be used instead of POST for queries
  • A query hash is to be passed directly in the query parameters
  • The ‘Request payload’ value will not be passed  in the query parameters
  • The BE is to cache requests coming from the FE side and store them under specific keys
  • If a query with such a key has already come before, the system must return the cached value to the FE part.
  • Cached requests must be refreshed at the frequency set in the system settings

  1. [BAT-II-0246] Varnish GQL

FEATURE SCOPE:

  • The Varnish cache accelerator is to be enabled for the BAT websites
  • Back end Entities that can be cached is to be identified and adapted for the Varnish accelerator
  • GraphCL schemas is to be modified for correct processing of cached results

  1. [BAT-II-0247] LUFT Upgrade

FEATURE SCOPE:

  • The LUFT app must be updated from 1.53 to the latest stable version at the release development launch date (25.06.21 - 1.71.3)
  • All relevant back end  modules must be updated as well
  • Full regression testing of the site's functionality must be carried out after the LUFT update
  • Based on the test results, all identified P1 and P2 bugs must be fixed
  • All other errors will be discussed separately and corrected as needed
  • As a result of the update, the following functions should be available and active:
  • JS Split
  • CSS Split
